      Id = "PatchNotesScreen_HideSpoilers"
      DisplayName = "{MX} HIDE SPOILERS"
    }

    /* Patch Notes */
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchSubHeading"
      DisplayName = "@GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#CommonFormat} - Change inspired by community feedback!"
    }
    /* Latest Patch Notes / New Patch Notes */
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes"
      DisplayName = "Patch Notes"
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotesTitle"
      DisplayName = "Patch Notes"
    }

    /* Roadmap / Development Roadmap */
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_Roadmap"
      DisplayName = "Coming Soon"
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II - Development Roadmap - June 2025

      After more than a year of {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access {#Prev}development, we're now starting to prepare for our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch!@GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Though we can't share too many details yet, read on for more about what you can expect.

      @GUI\\HorizontalDividerLong

      {#AlertH2Format}Latest Progress: {#Prev}We've launched our third {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}in {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access{#Prev}, featuring all-new Hidden Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms, variations of every Guardian Encounter, and more!

      {#AlertH2Format}Our v1.0 Launch is Coming Up: {#Prev}We're heading into the final phase of {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II {#Prev}development, which involves adding the story's true ending and other finishing touches.

      {#AlertH2Format}We Don't Have a v1.0 Launch Date Yet: {#Prev}It's too early to announce a timeframe for our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch, though we'll share more as soon as we can. We really appreciate your patience on this!

      @GUI\\HorizontalDividerLong

      As we wind down our {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access {#Prev}phase, our goal remains ensuring we've created our biggest, most replayable, most feature-rich game yet, and — most importantly — a worthy successor to the original {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades{#Prev}.

      {#AlertH2Format}High Priority Tasks: {#Prev}These are major initiatives we're working on.

      @GUI\\Shell\\selector {#AlertHighlightFormat}The True Ending: {#Prev}The conclusion of Princess Melinoë's story is the main addition we're planning for our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch. We have no plans for additional regions, encounters, abilities, and so on.

      @GUI\\Shell\\selector {#AlertHighlightFormat}Achievements: {#Prev}With the game structure fully intact, we'll be adding Achievements in the lead-up to launch. Note you will {#AlertItalicFormat}not {#Prev}need to start from the beginning to earn any Achievements.

      @GUI\\Shell\\selector {#AlertHighlightFormat}Finishing Touches: {#Prev}We're continuing to polish and refine all the content we've introduced in {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II{#Prev}, from Boons and powers to artwork and story events.

      Sometimes the last stretch of development on a game can make all the difference, so we have always taken this phase seriously and appreciate your continued support.

      @GUI\\HorizontalDividerLong

      {#AlertH2Format}Disclosures: {#Prev}Please bear in mind {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II {#Prev}is a work-in-progress. While we consider many parts of the game complete or nearly so, other parts may keep changing and improving to an extent.

      If you end up playing quite a bit, know that we will be doing everything possible to ensure your {#AlertBoldFormat}Save Data {#Prev}works all through our {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access {#Prev}into our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch!

    @GUI\\HorizontalDividerLong

      {#AlertH2Format}Closing Remarks: {#Prev}We have a big game to wrap up! While we can't yet say when our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch will be, we're very excited to be getting close, and to share the complete experience with you.

      This also means some of the most important work on {#AlertHeaderFormat}Hades II {#Prev}is still to come, so {#AlertItalicFormat}may moonlight guide us! {#Prev}And to all our {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access {#Prev}players, thank you for being here. 

    @GUI\\SGLogo_Roadmap
    """
    }

    /* Hades II Patch Notes */
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0011"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 11 - July 23, 2025
      {#AlertItalicFormat}Surprise! {#Prev}While we said our prior patch would {#AlertItalicFormat}likely {#Prev}be our last before our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch, as the Fates would have it, there is indeed this one more, which includes further improvements, balance adjustments, and fixes based on your feedback and what we've observed. Thank you for playing in {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access{#Prev}!

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Notice: {#Prev}In preparation for our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch and forthcoming story sequences surrounding the True Ending, please note that any {#AlertBoldFormat}Zodiac Sand {#Prev}or {#AlertBoldFormat}Void Lens {#Prev}resources you have when you load your save progress at that time will automatically be converted to {#AlertBoldFormat}Prestige{#Prev}. For now, you may continue earning these if you wish.

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames{#Prev}: increased Special projectile size and orbit speed 
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe{#Prev}: increased damage of Attack sequence
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat{#Prev}: improved responsiveness of blocking while channeling Omega Attack

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis){#Prev}: reduced recharge time for Riposte effect, so it can be used more frequently
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Melinoë){#Prev}: increased Critical damage chance
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Eos){#Prev}: using Special no longer cancels other Special projectiles; improved target tracking of Daybreaker projectile
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe (Thanatos){#Prev}: increased Critical chance ramp-up and upper limit
      · {#Spoiler}Witch's Staff (Anubis){#Prev}: increased Magick cost of Omega Special
      · {#Spoiler}Umbral Flames (Supay){#Prev}: reworked Special creates a second projectile; reworked Attack timings and Omega Attack; shots no longer stagger foes; reduced Rush Boon damage bonus; now breaks Urns more easily
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat (Shiva){#Prev}: reworked Omega Special bounces several times in the target area; reduced Destructive damage bonus to compensate

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Storm Ring (Zeus){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Arc Flash (Zeus){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tidal Ring (Poseidon){#Prev}: reduced damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}High Surf (Poseidon){#Prev}: reduced area of effect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Solar Ring (Apollo){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hephaestus{#Prev}: increased damage of Blast effects, such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Smithy Rush{#Prev}; increased Glow bonus from Rarity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tough Gain (Hephaestus){#Prev}: effect now activates even if you are protected by {#AlertBoldFormat}Paid Dues (Hermes)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Molten Touch (Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased damage to Armor, increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heat Rush (Hestia){#Prev}: slightly reduced duration of damage trail
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares{#Prev}: Plasma can no longer grant more than +100% move and strike speed, which caused various issues
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Golden Rule (Hera x Poseidon){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ripple Effect (Hera x Poseidon){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your effects from {#AlertBoldFormat}Fine Line (Hera) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Ocean Swell (Poseidon) {#Prev}have a chance to fire twice
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Seismic Hammer (Poseidon x Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Seismic Servo (Poseidon x Hephaestus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Any Boon effects that recharge over time recharge faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Room Temperature (Demeter x Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cryo Pounder (Demeter x Hephaestus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your blasts from Hephaestus deal more damage to Freeze-afflicted foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rude Awakening (Apollo x Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased bonus damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Chain Reaction (Hephaestus x Hestia){#Prev}: increased timing window of Double Blast effect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Travel Deal (Hermes){#Prev}: reduced Gold discount
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Harm for the Afflicted (Medea){#Prev}: increased how frequently this can deal damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Suffering on Sight (Medea){#Prev}: increased average damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Old Herbal Remedy (Circe){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing this effect to not be reduced by {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Scars (Oath)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Protective Coating (Icarus){#Prev}: increased Armor
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Volatile Coating (Icarus){#Prev}: increased Armor and blast damage

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Inverted Spark (Flames){#Prev}: improved compatibility with more Aspects
      · {#Spoiler}Helheim Charge (Skull){#Prev}: now fires your Omega Attack an additional time in succession
      · {#Spoiler}Chakra Collider (Coat){#Prev}: increased Power Shot timing window
      · {#Spoiler}Awakened Rockets (Coat){#Prev}: increased Magick cost

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes & Path of Stars{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Reduced start-up time of most Hexes, making them faster to use
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Godsent {#Prev}upgrades now can appear on subsequent uses of the Path of Stars, if you meet the required Olympian after prior uses
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Confluence (Night Bloom){#Prev}: now makes your raised servants appear in your Casts, not after you Sprint
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved menu navigation of the Path of Stars while using gamepad controls

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Olympian Keepsakes such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Cloud Bangle (Zeus) {#Prev}activate more reliably in {#AlertBoldFormat}Thessaly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ghost Onion{#Prev}: restorative effect is no longer reduced by {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Scars (Oath)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crystal Figurine{#Prev}: now activates an additional random Arcana Card

      {#AlertH2Format}Animal Familiars{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Toula the Cat{#Prev}: improved bonuses from Familiar Bonds, and innate movement speed, pounce accuracy, and active time between naps; she is also less prone to getting stuck on obstacles
      · Removed {#AlertHighlightFormat}Attending a Faithful Beast (Cauldron) {#Prev}, along with associated bonuses from Resting your Familiars

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Dangers{#Prev}
      · Encounters on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus {#Prev}now have slightly fewer foes
      · Encounters with {#AlertBoldFormat}Icarus {#Prev}have slightly fewer foes at the same time
      · Encounters on the {#AlertBoldFormat}Summit {#Prev}now have slightly fewer foes; some smaller foes have slightly increased Life
      · Foes from {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monuments {#Prev}now have more Armor in later Regions 
      · {#Spoiler}Typhon{#Prev}: reduced speed and damage of main eye blast; reduced duration of some projectiles; reduced frequency of cyclone attacks in second phase
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prometheus{#Prev}: reduced tracking speed of uppercut
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Cerberus{#Prev}: no longer also drops magma on top of his attacks
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Scylla{#Prev}: the guest artist fires fewer projectiles than before
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Hecate{#Prev}: fixed an issue causing the real {#Spoiler}Hecate {#Prev}to be easier to distinguish from the other two, unlike in the standard Encounter
      · {#Spoiler}Master-Slicer (Erebus){#Prev}: reduced Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lurker (Oceanus){#Prev}: attacks can be blocked more reliably using the {#AlertBoldFormat}Black Coat
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shellback (Oceanus){#Prev}: Elite now shoots a larger bouncing projectile instead of a triple-shot
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Holeheart (Fields){#Prev}: thrown bomb no longer deals direct damage; Elite no longer throws multiples at once
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Brush-Stalker (Fields){#Prev}: reduced maximum targeting distance for ranged attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lycaon (Fields){#Prev}: pounce attack now is slower to start
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Goldwraith (Tartarus){#Prev}: slightly reduced appearance rate
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tempus (Tartarus){#Prev}: slightly reduced appearance rate
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sandskull (Tartarus){#Prev}: slightly reduced appearance rate
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Satyr Hoplite (Olympus) {#Prev}: Elite throws fewer projectiles at once
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Satyr Vierophant (Tartarus){#Prev}: adjusted summoning behavior; reduced duration of fireball and its damage trail
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shambler{#Prev}: all varieties have reduced tracking speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bronzebeak (Ephyra){#Prev}: adjusted attack behavior
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lubber (Ephyra){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing their flames to sometimes destroy your projectiles
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eidolon (Ephyra){#Prev}: Elite no longer throws multiple projectiles at once
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Droplet (Thessaly) {#Prev}: reduced move speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Stickler (Thessaly) {#Prev}: reduced projectile speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Boozer (Thessaly) {#Prev}: reduced lunge-attack distance and accuracy
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Harpy Talon (Thessaly) {#Prev}: removed cyclone attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Auto-Seeker (Olympus) {#Prev}: removed self-destruct attack; reduced number of shots but increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Auto-Forcer (Olympus) {#Prev}: reduced move speed during whirlwind attack; increased recovery time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sky-Dracon (Olympus) {#Prev}: removed flame-breath attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mega-Dracon (Olympus) {#Prev}: updated flame-breath attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Satyr Goldpike (Olympus) {#Prev}: Elite throws fewer projectiles at once
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Satyr Sapper (Olympus) {#Prev}: reduced speed and range of rocket attack; Elite fires fewer rockets

      {#AlertH2Format}Level Design & Environments{#Prev}
      · Several Locations on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus {#Prev}now have more places to take cover against enemy fire
      · Improved pathing and collision in several Locations

      {#AlertH2Format}Book of Shadows{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved sorting of Path of Stars upgrades for {#AlertBoldFormat}Selene {#Prev}after the Incantation {#AlertBoldFormat}Insight Into Offerings

      {#AlertH2Format}Art & Visual FX{#Prev}
      · Further adjustments to visual FX of various strikes and abilities to improve visual clarity in combat
      · Other minor fixes and improvements

      {#AlertH2Format}Voice & Narrative{#Prev}
      · Updated voiceover for {#AlertBoldFormat}Athena

      {#AlertH2Format}Music & SFX{#Prev}
      · Improved audio feedback for Power Shot effects
      · Updated sound effects for {#Spoiler}Umbral Flames (Supay)
      · Other minor improvements

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You can no longer lose all your Life in the brief time it takes {#AlertBoldFormat}Athena {#Prev}to arrive once she is on her way
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You can no longer lose all your Life between clearing a Chaos Trial and being sent back by {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Your raised servants now show damage numbers when their strikes connect
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You can no longer Deflect raised {#AlertBoldFormat}Tempii {#Prev}attempting to heal you in the Encounter against {#Spoiler}Chronos
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved feedback on some Boons or items whose Life restoration is reduced by {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Scars
      · Clarified that {#AlertBoldFormat}Gift Gift Gift (Echo) {#Prev}requires switching Keepsakes to take effect
      · Updated {#AlertBoldFormat}Credits {#Prev}with additional contributors
      · Updates and fixes to translations in some languages

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      · Fixed an issue causing the Rush Boon bonus from {#Spoiler}Umbral Flames (Supay) {#Prev}to affect indirect Boons such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Beach Ball (Poseidon x Apollo)
      · Fixed an issue causing Blast effects from {#AlertBoldFormat}Hephaestus {#Prev}to gain 'strike foes from behind' bonuses
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Ionic Gain (Zeus) {#Prev}Aether Fonts appearing in unreachable places in the {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Eris {#Prev}Encounter
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Blinding Rush (Apollo) {#Prev}or other Daze effects not affecting {#Spoiler}Typhon
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interaction with various Aspects and {#AlertBoldFormat}Exceptional Talent (Apollo)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Buried Treasure (Poseidon) {#Prev}or {#AlertBoldFormat}Quick Buck (Hermes) {#Prev}items sometimes being out of reach
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Whispered Prayer (Artemis) {#Prev}not improving with Rarity
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interactions with {#Spoiler}Witch's Staff (Anubis) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Wave Strike (Poseidon) {#Prev}or {#AlertBoldFormat}Cardio Gain (Hestia)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Purification (Phase Shift) {#Prev}destroying your projectiles from {#Spoiler}Black Coat (Shiva)
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Gigaros Dash (Hades) {#Prev}amplifying damage other than Attack and Special
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Full Service (Icarus) {#Prev}not improving {#AlertBoldFormat}Rapid Slash (Daedalus - Axe)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Mega Blaze (Daedalus - Flames) {#Prev}not affecting Omega Attack as described
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Garmr Gaze (Daedalus - Skull) {#Prev}reducing range unexpectedly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Ambition (Sky Fall) {#Prev}not working against Guardians as described
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a rare case where {#Spoiler}Typhon {#Prev}could remain impervious indefinitely...
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Scylla {#Prev}sometimes stage-diving into the walls and getting stuck...
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}sometimes speaking over the Pause Menu even while absent in the {#Spoiler}Typhon {#Prev}Encounter
      · Fixed various issues with foes summoned by {#Spoiler}Typhon
      · Fixed several cases where Olympian effects could appear on impervious foes
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Voice of Truth {#Prev}Prophecy missing a requirement for {#AlertBoldFormat}Gold Gold Gold (Echo)
      · Fixed text not fading out as expected during the narrated {#AlertBoldFormat}Homer {#Prev}outcomes after a successful clear
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed various voice lines and story events playing unexpectedly or not playing when expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed occasional visual issues with Magick Indicator while using {#AlertBoldFormat}Black Coat (Nyx)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text errors
      · Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'Thirsty for water, \[Narcissus\] started to drink, but soon grew thirsty for something else. His being was suddenly overwhelmed by a vision of beauty. He fell in love with an empty hope, a shadow mistaken for substance.'

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Metamorphoses {#QuoteBaseFormat}(Ovid; D. Raeburn translation)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0010"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 10 - July 2, 2025
      Thank you for playing our recent {#AlertHighlightFormat}Unseen Update{#Prev}! This patch makes a number of adjustments to some of the latest additions. We'll keep monitoring your feedback, though this will likely be our final patch before our {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch, whenever that will be! We're very grateful for your support throughout {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access{#Prev}!

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      · Reduced further cases of successive attacks causing you to become 'stun-locked'
      · Whenever you take damage to Armor, it will reduce any temporary Armor you have from sources such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Security System (Hephaestus){#Prev}, prior to reducing the more-permanent kind

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: Omega Attack can no longer be interrupted by foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames{#Prev}: reduced orbit speed of Omega Special projectiles, but increased their damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull{#Prev}: Omega Special wave projectiles no longer stagger foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat{#Prev}: increased speed of Attack sequence and damage of first strike; slightly increased Omega Attack channel speed, and it can block more types of incoming area-effect damage; increased Special accuracy

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Melinoë){#Prev}: reduced bonus to Magick and Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Momus){#Prev}: slightly increased how long it takes your serpents to fire successive Omega Moves
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Pan){#Prev}: it now is easier to Dash out of recovery times
      · {#Spoiler}Sister Blades (Morrigan){#Prev}: improved input buffering, reducing cases of dropped inputs during combat
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Moros){#Prev}: adjusted projectile speeds; aligned Omega Attack damage with base Aspect 
      · {#Spoiler}Umbral Flames (Supay){#Prev}: reduced projectiles from Attacks and Specials, but increased their damage; reduced Rush Boon damage bonus
      · {#Spoiler}Moonstone Axe (Nergal){#Prev}: slightly reduced Dash-Strike damage; slightly increased Attack damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Medea){#Prev}: slightly reduced area of Attacks, which still is greater than the base Aspect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Persephone){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing Boons to gain bonus Lv. more often than intended
      · {#Spoiler}Argent Skull (Hel){#Prev}: now breaks Urns more easily
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat (Nyx){#Prev}: increased Omega Boost damage; increased damage of Special Nightspawns
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat (Shiva){#Prev}: reworked Destructive effect now makes Omega Attack deal bonus damage; increased Special damage; normalized Omega Special travel time, reticle remains until the blast

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Frenzy{#Prev}: now also makes foes enter the battle faster; reduced effect on {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Rivals {#Prev}moves
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Scars{#Prev}: fixed several cases where this was not reducing Life recovery as expected

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steady Growth (Demeter){#Prev}: now will only Rarify itself if you have no other eligible Boons
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hestia{#Prev}: Scorch Curse can no longer deal Critical damage or similar, nor is affected by {#AlertBoldFormat}Air Quality (Zeus)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flame Strike (Hestia){#Prev}: slightly reduced Scorch damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flame Flourish (Hestia){#Prev}: slightly reduced Scorch damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Success Rate (Hermes){#Prev}: no longer affects the passive effect of {#AlertBoldFormat}Raki
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Incandescent Aura (Hera x Hestia){#Prev}: reworked — now deals damage to all Hitch-afflicted foes when you restore Magick
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Natural Selection (Poseidon x Demeter){#Prev}: reworked — now distributes bonus Lv. to your primary Boons
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Scalding Vapor (Poseidon x Hestia){#Prev}: no longer can activate the Froth Curse
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gigaros Dash (Hades){#Prev}: reduced damage; fixed Scorn amplifying damage other than Attack and Special
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Unseen Ire (Hades){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing the effect duration to last longer than stated
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crimson Dress (Arachne){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing this to give a high damage bonus right away; increased bonus per Encounter

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Boosted Ignition (Skull){#Prev}: no longer offered while using {#Spoiler}Aspect of Hel
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Looming Ignition (Skull){#Prev}: fixed an issue causing this to give its full damage bonus immediately rather than over the duration as described
      · {#Spoiler}Pharaoh Etchings (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lone Shades deal more damage and automatically launch at foes struck by your Omega Special
      · {#Spoiler}Sinister Pinion (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials repeatedly deal damage faster
      · {#Spoiler}Helheim Charge (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Attack fires twice in succession
      · {#Spoiler}Chakra Collider (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Attack gains a Power Shot that deals heavy damage

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes & Path of Stars{#Prev}      
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Adjusted {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}layouts to make room especially for {#AlertBoldFormat}Godsent {#Prev}upgrades
      · Adjusted when {#AlertBoldFormat}Godsent {#Prev}upgrades are offered during the story for the first time, now later than before
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Twilight Curse{#Prev}: this and other Morph effects now block any on-death attacks when afflicted foes are slain, with the exception of Inferno-Bombs
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prize of Poseidon (Moon Water){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with... 
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Pride of Poseidon (Moon Water){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade gradually restores Life and Magick over time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Zenith (Sky Fall){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with {#AlertBoldFormat}Ambition{#Prev}, which deals bonus damage to Guardians
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lineage{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Hex can be {#AlertBoldFormat}Godsent {#Prev}one more time when used in Guardian Encounters

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Discordant Bell{#Prev}: effect now persists for the night even after you switch Keepsakes

      {#AlertH2Format}Resources & Reagents{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Reduced chance of never finding the resource type aligned with your {#AlertBoldFormat}Animal Familiar {#Prev}in shorter regions

      {#AlertH2Format}Shrine of Hermes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fresh Sustenance MAX{#Prev}: reduced Life recovery

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Dangers{#Prev}
      · Various adjustments to the new {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Rivals {#Prev}Encounters, including...
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Typhon{#Prev}: adjusted behaviors of {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}, who should no longer teleport in the middle of his strikes; adjusted patterns in final phase
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Chronos{#Prev}: adjusted various behaviors; adjusted hitbox of Swipe attack; {#Spoiler}Tempii {#Prev}no longer heal when affected by {#AlertBoldFormat}Twilight Curse (Selene){#Prev}; now summons only a single Warden
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Prometheus{#Prev}: adjusted various behaviors of {#Spoiler}both combatants{#Prev}; {#Spoiler}Heracles {#Prev}has reduced Life; {#Spoiler}Aetos now briefly takes over if Prometheus is vanquished first
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Cerberus{#Prev}: updated behaviors in the initial phase
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Eris{#Prev}: adjusted various behaviors; reduced how much of the field gets engulfed in flame
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Scylla{#Prev}: adjusted various behaviors of {#Spoiler}each member of the band
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Polyphemus{#Prev}: adjusted various behaviors including his Grab move; {#Spoiler}Curing Pools {#Prev}now clear nearby {#Spoiler}poison {#Prev}when used, can be used more frequently, and can no longer can be destroyed
      · {#Spoiler}Unrivaled Hecate{#Prev}: increased effectiveness of mid-phase moves; reduced tracking and hit-stun on projectiles from {#Spoiler}Dark Side {#Prev}and Sisters of the Dead

      {#AlertH2Format}Art & Visual FX{#Prev}
      · Added alternate textures when using upgraded Tools of the Unseen
      · Added visual FX to {#Spoiler}Typhon's Eggs
      · Updated visual FX when {#AlertBoldFormat}Crescent Pick {#Prev}Outcroppings are depleted
      · Added visual indicator in Boon Info for when Arcana are disabled due to {#AlertBoldFormat}Barren (Chaos)

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Melinoë now can greet Frinos while he is in the Training Grounds, as with the other Animal Familiars
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Gameplay Timer now also pauses automatically when interacting with the {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles {#Prev}no longer sometimes ominously just stands around after his Encounters
      · Updated presentation for {#AlertBoldFormat}Icarus {#Prev}fly-by attacks
      · Improved feedback on Life and Magick gauges after swapping Keepsakes that modify your totals
      · Improved feedback spending resources in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Silver Pool{#Prev}, and {#AlertBoldFormat}Music Maker {#Prev}screens
      · Improved contextual feedback on various Boons when affected by {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Scars
      · Damage from Specials and Omega Specials is now separated for some weapons on the {#AlertBoldFormat}Victory Screen
      · Reduced cluttered damage numbers using {#AlertBoldFormat}Argent Skull (Medea)
      · Added letterbox to the game intro in some aspect ratios
      · Updates and fixes to translations in some languages

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed an issue where Melinoë could suddenly take 500 damage using {#AlertBoldFormat}Eruption (Path of Stars) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Night Bloom (Selene) {#Prev}to raise a Tempus in the battle against Chronos...
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a number of story events that were never playing
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a number of contextual voice lines that were never playing
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed cases where you would sometimes Dash-Strike unexpectedly using the {#AlertBoldFormat}Moonstone Axe
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed some interactions between {#Spoiler}Moonstone Axe (Nergal) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Psychic Whirlwind (Daedalus)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Black Coat {#Prev}not interacting with some abilities that improved Channeling speed
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed visual issues where strikes with Hidden Aspects sometimes appeared to be interrupted by foes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Wounds from {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares {#Prev}sometimes causing on-hit slowdowns too frequently
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Sea Star (Poseidon) {#Prev}sometimes doubling items created by {#AlertBoldFormat}Gold Gold Gold (Echo)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Personal Loan (Dionysus) {#Prev}giving you nothing back if it got Rarified
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles {#Prev}sometimes turning invisible while attacking
      · Fixed cases where {#AlertBoldFormat}Athena {#Prev}could unexpectedly appear more than once per night
      · Fixed {#Spoiler}Typhon {#Prev}sometimes not taking damage from raised servants as expected
      · Fixed cases where using Cast to interrupt Attacks or Specials would pause animations longer than expected
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Past Deeds {#Prev}screen not showing more than 36 Boons if you had that many 
      · Fixed Satyr Supplicant Life Bars persisting after they were slain
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares {#Prev}Plasma UI indicator sometimes disappearing unexpectedly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text errors
      · Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'In the past he wandered endlessly over the boundless earth and sea on missions ordered by lord Eurystheus; his reckless deeds were many and many the ordeals he suffered.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~The Homeric Hymns, 15: To Lion-Hearted Herakles {#QuoteBaseFormat}(Homer; A. Athanassakis translation)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0009"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 9: The UNSEEN Update - June 17, 2025

      Our third {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}in {#AlertHighlightFormat}Early Access {#Prev}is now available, featuring an all-new Hidden Aspect for {#AlertItalicFormat}each {#Prev}of the Nocturnal Arms, a unique new variation of {#AlertItalicFormat}each {#Prev}Guardian Encounter, and plenty of new story events, artwork, music, and more! Please check our {#AlertBoldFormat}Development Roadmap {#Prev}for important details about our eventual {#AlertHighlightFormat}v1.0 {#Prev}launch, and we'll be keeping a close eye on your feedback as we continue on!

      {#AlertH2Format}Highlights{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hidden Aspects{#Prev}: Each of the Nocturnal Arms now has a secret, final form to discover...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Rivals{#Prev}: Reveal this in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Oath of the Unseen {#Prev}for all-new challenges from each Guardian
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Revamped Umbral Flames{#Prev}: The Flames of Ygnium now offer a smoother, snappier fighting style
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Godsent Hexes{#Prev}: The {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}now can infuse each Selene Hex with a unique new Olympian power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Forge Bonds{#Prev}: Grow closer than ever before to a variety of characters in numerous new optional events
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Wardens{#Prev}: Watch out for powerful new foes in Erebus and the City of Ephyra
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shinier Artwork{#Prev}: Look for many new visual flourishes such as ambient effects on most character portraits
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Music{#Prev}: Listen for new pieces including a hot new single from a certain band...

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      · In standard Encounters, new waves of foes now spawn slightly sooner, reducing downtime
      · Your melee strikes are no longer negated by certain obstacles {#AlertItalicFormat}(foes behind them now get hit)
      · Many attacks that briefly stunned you now slow you instead, reducing cases of being 'stun-locked'
      · You now may exit Locations slightly sooner than before, right after collecting Rewards
      · Melinoë's Olympic Slam entrances on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus {#Prev}are faster and hit a slightly wider area
      · Removed the infrequent second stage of {#AlertBoldFormat}Rod of Fishing {#Prev}sequences; the initial interaction is unchanged

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: increased Omega Special damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames{#Prev}: reworked — adjusted properties of Attacks and Specials for improved flow and feel
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat{#Prev}: increased Attack, Omega Attack, and Omega Special damage

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Witch's Staff (Anubis){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Create damaging fields, draw foes in, and use Lone Shades to your advantage
      · {#Spoiler}Sister Blades (Morrigan){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Perform the devastating Blood Triad after landing your other moves
      · {#Spoiler}Umbral Flames (Supay){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Fire on foes automatically, supercharging your shots when necessary
      · {#Spoiler}Moonstone Axe (Nergal){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Obliterate your foes with heavy strikes, and go berserk to restore Life
      · {#Spoiler}Argent Skull (Hel){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Fire continually without the need for Shells
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat (Shiva){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Absorb your Omega Special blasts to destroy your foes when their Life runs low
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Melinoë){#Prev}: reworked — now raises Magick and adds Power to your Specials
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Circe){#Prev}: reworked — whenever you use Casts, so does your Animal Familiar; this creates a Psychic Leash between you that damages foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Pan){#Prev}: Omega Special recovery time now scales with the number of blades thrown
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Melinoë){#Prev}: reworked — now adds Critical damage chance to your Attacks and Specials  
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe (Charon){#Prev}: no longer increases duration of your Casts
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Persephone){#Prev}: bonus Omega Special duration now charges from Olympian damage; reworked passive benefit now automatically raises Boon Lv.
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat (Nyx){#Prev}: Nightspawn hits now also activate Olympian effects from the strike you used

      {#AlertH2Format}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Excellence{#Prev}: now also increases the chance of finding Legendary Boons
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Strength{#Prev}: reduced damage resistance and bonus damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Divinity{#Prev}: reduced chance of improved Rarity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Unseen{#Prev}: improved Magick restoration
      · While in Insights mode, you now can Inspect max-rank Arcana Cards for a closer look
      · Adjusted upgrade costs of some Arcana Cards

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Rivals{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Makes each Guardian more challenging in unique ways; the first Rank affects the first Guardian of both the Underworld and Surface routes; prevail against both to reveal the next Rank, and so on
      · Reduced Fear required for Surface victories to become {#Spoiler}Night's Champion {#Prev}according to {#AlertBoldFormat}Schelemeus
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Added contextual feedback when Life restoration effects are being reduced by the {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Scars
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack The stasis effect from the {#AlertBoldFormat}Stopper {#Prev}Perk from the {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Fangs {#Prev}now is easier to anticipate      

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Air Quality (Zeus){#Prev}: increased damage minimum
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Poseidon{#Prev}: Slip Curse replaced with {#AlertBoldFormat}Froth{#Prev}, which can make foes take a burst of damage when struck
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tidal Ring (Poseidon){#Prev}: now hits foes in the binding circle instead of ahead, and inflicts Froth
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Breaker Rush (Poseidon){#Prev}: now deals more damage, and in an area around you
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fluid Gain (Poseidon){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flood Gain (Poseidon){#Prev}: your Omega Moves briefly restore any Magick used, repeatable after a delay
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sea Star (Poseidon){#Prev}: increased effect chance
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}High Surf (Poseidon){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Depth Charge (Poseidon){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ocean Swell (Poseidon){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Moves also launch a damaging wave, but use more Magick
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Slippery Slope (Poseidon){#Prev}: now also makes Froth deal more damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prominence Flare (Apollo){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tranquil Gain (Demeter){#Prev}: Magick restoration effect starts sooner and is faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Frosty Veneer (Demeter){#Prev}: now reduces heavy damage above a certain threshold rather than capping it
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Aphrodite{#Prev}: reduced duration of her Weak Curse
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Life Affirmation (Aphrodite){#Prev}: cut from game {#AlertItalicFormat}(sort of){#Prev}; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spiritual Affirmation (Aphrodite){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Gain max Life and Magick, and future increases are worth more
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shameless Attitude (Aphrodite){#Prev}: reduced bonus damage
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hephaestus{#Prev}: Vent Curse replaced with {#AlertBoldFormat}Glow{#Prev}, which makes foes take bonus damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Volcanic Strike (Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Volcanic Flourish (Hephaestus){#Prev}: slightly reduced recharge time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Uncanny Fortitude (Hephaestus){#Prev}: reduced Life gain
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mint Condition (Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game {#AlertItalicFormat}(sort of){#Prev}; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Security System (Hephaestus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}At the start of each Encounter, gain a lot of Armor, but only briefly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heavy Metal (Hephaestus){#Prev}: reworked — gain Armor and deal more weapon damage based on it
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hestia{#Prev}: Increased damage rate of her Scorch Curse; fixed Scorch not counting as a damaging effect from Olympians, for interactions with Boons such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Rallying Cry (Ares)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flame Flourish (Hestia){#Prev}: increased Scorch damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heat Rush (Hestia){#Prev}: reworked — now leaves a damaging trail, and reduces damage you take from burning
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Burnt Offering (Hestia){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Snuffed Candle (Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Deal bonus damage to isolated foes; previously {#AlertBoldFormat}Single Elimination (Ares)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fire Walk (Hestia){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fire Away (Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new Legendary! {#Prev}Your Casts destroy many foes' ranged shots and inflict {#AlertBoldFormat}Scorch
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares{#Prev}: Improved visual clarity of Blood Drops, now called {#AlertBoldFormat}Plasma
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mortal Gain (Ares){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Grisly Gain (Ares){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Striking foes may spill Plasma, which also restores Magick when collected
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Single Elimination (Ares){#Prev}: cut from game; this effect now is on a new {#AlertBoldFormat}Hestia {#Prev}Boon, {#AlertBoldFormat}Snuffed Candle
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mean Streak (Hermes){#Prev}: increased duration of stacking damage bonus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Easy Shot (Artemis){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shadow Pounce (Artemis){#Prev}: now gives Omega Moves a chance to deal Critical damage after you Dash
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Whispered Prayer (Artemis){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Hex may deal Critical damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Divine Dash (Athena){#Prev}: reduced Deflect duration to match the original game
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Task Force (Athena){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Godsent Hexes can be used more times per Encounter
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Worry Free (Dionysus){#Prev}: now gives a random amount of bonus Life within a range, rather than a set amount
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Personal Loan (Dionysus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Give up all your Gold; after the next Guardian, gain it back, with interest!
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Reckless Abandon (Dionysus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attacks deal random damage from a set range of values
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cinerary Circle (Hades){#Prev}: now spawns fewer, stronger Soul Urns that hit a wider area
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gigaros Dash (Hades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Dash damages surrounding foes and briefly makes them take more damage from your Attack and Special
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Unseen Ire (Hades){#Prev}: no longer one of his initial offerings, but is offered after a certain point
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonlight Dress (Arachne){#Prev}: reworked — Outfit makes your Hexes charge using less Magick than before; the previous effect is now called {#AlertBoldFormat}Gilded Dress
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crimson Dress (Arachne){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Outfit makes you deal more damage after each Encounter
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gold Gold Gold (Echo){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}After your next purchase from Charon, gain another at no extra charge
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gift Gift Gift (Echo){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}In the next Region, gain the basic effect of your current Keepsake 
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Harm for the Afflicted (Medea){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Inflicting Curses also deals damage to unafflicted foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Word of Greater Girth (Circe){#Prev}: now also raises your max Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hymn to the Eye of Night (Circe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Hex deals bonus damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Turning to a Simple Form (Circe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Moves have a chance to inflict Morph
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ingenious Strike (Icarus){#Prev}: reworked — now gives bonus Lv. to your Attack Boon
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ingenious Flourish (Icarus){#Prev}: reworked — now gives bonus Lv. to your Special Boon
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Full Service (Icarus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}One of your Hammer enchantments is upgraded to Rank II
      · {#AlertItalicFormat}Note: {#Prev}Several of the new blessings noted above require first having reached a certain point in your relationship with the corresponding character
      · Also adjusted power levels of various {#AlertBoldFormat}Duo {#Prev}Boons, including...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Thermal Dynamics (Zeus x Hestia){#Prev}: increased Scorch damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Golden Rule (Hera x Poseidon){#Prev}: increased bonus damage from Gold
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Brave Face (Hera x Hephaestus){#Prev}: reduced damage resistance from Magick
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Incandescent Aura (Hera x Hestia){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Natural Selection (Poseidon x Demeter){#Prev}: increased chance of improved Rarity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Scalding Vapor (Poseidon x Hestia){#Prev}: adjusted to work with the new Froth Curse
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Love Handles (Aphrodite x Hephaestus){#Prev}: reduced Heartthrob damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Carnal Pleasure (Aphrodite x Ares){#Prev}: now has a chance of creating a Heartthrob instead of guaranteeing one
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Chain Reaction (Hephaestus x Hestia){#Prev}: reduced timing window for the effect
      · Removed several cases where Boons affecting your Cast prevented other such Boons from being offered
      · Additional adjustments to some Boon bonuses from Rarity and {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · Further clarifications to descriptions for various Boons
      · Various other minor fixes and adjustments

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Melting Swipe (Staff){#Prev}: reworked — Your Dash-Strike now deals heavy damage to Armor, instead of destroying a percentage of the total; adjusted {#AlertBoldFormat}Melting {#Prev}upgrades for other weapons accordingly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hidden Helix (Flames){#Prev}: reworked — Your Specials create a bonus projectile; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Triple Helix
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Enduring Coil (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Special lasts longer
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Possessed Array (Skull){#Prev}: losing Magick from retrieving Shells no longer charges your Hex
      · Added unique enchantments for Hidden Aspects, replacing ones that do not work with them, including:
      · {#Spoiler}Mirrored Ankh (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Attack creates another damage field ahead of the first
      · {#Spoiler}Soulfilled Ankh (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attacks gain Power and hit a larger area
      · {#Spoiler}Scarab Etchings (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Lone Shades deal bonus damage and may reappear after they hit
      · {#Spoiler}Phantom Etchings (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Blood Triad combo deals even more damage
      · {#Spoiler}Banshee Brand (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Blood Triad combo has a chance to strike once more
      · {#Spoiler}Demonic Cell (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}As long as you Sprint, your Attacks and Specials have bonus Power
      · {#Spoiler}Heaven Splitter (Axe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attack hits multiple times, but you can only perform the first slam
      · {#Spoiler}Iron Core (Axe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Berserk effect lasts longer and restores more Life per foe struck
      · {#Spoiler}Garmr Gaze (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attacks shoot farther and deal bonus damage
      · {#Spoiler}Leering Glance (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attack shots bounce to one more foe and deal bonus damage on that hit
      · {#Spoiler}Runic Driver (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials fly faster and deal more damage for each foe struck
      · {#Spoiler}Venerated Relic (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Valkyrie effect lasts longer
      · {#Spoiler}Nirvana Engine (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}During your Destructive effect, you can destroy foes with more Life
      · {#Spoiler}Elephant Rockets (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials have more Power and fly straight ahead
      · {#Spoiler}Counter Supreme (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}After blocking with your Omega Attack, become Destructive
      · {#Spoiler}Awakened Rockets (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Absorbing blasts from your Omega Special also fires your Special
      · {#Spoiler}Mooncrest Riser (Coat){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Dash-Strike hits a larger area and deals bonus damage
      · Adjusted names and descriptions for several Daedalus Hammer upgrades

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes & Path of Stars{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Temper of Zeus{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes your {#AlertBoldFormat}Twilight Curse {#Prev}shot strike foes near it with lightning
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nurture of Hera{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes your {#AlertBoldFormat}Night Bloom {#Prev}servant faster and stronger
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prize of Poseidon{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Water {#Prev}also create several restorative items
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Squall of Demeter{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes all foes take damage during {#AlertBoldFormat}Phase Shift
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shine of Apollo{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Lunar Ray {#Prev}fire a bigger solar-infused beam
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Allure of Aphrodite{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes you keep spawning Heartthrobs during {#AlertBoldFormat}Dark Side
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hand of Hephaestus{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Godsent upgrade makes you deal a damaging blast after using {#AlertBoldFormat}Wolf Howl
