      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0008"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 8 - February 26, 2025

      We appreciate all the feedback following last week's {#AlertHighlightFormat}Warsong Update{#Prev}! This patch includes fixes and targeted adjustments for a smoother play experience as you battle toward the final confrontation. We're now shifting focus to our {#AlertItalicFormat}third {#Prev}{#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}outlined in our {#AlertBoldFormat}Roadmap{#Prev}. Until then, thank you for playing!

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: slightly increased speed of the first two strikes in the Attack sequence
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull{#Prev}: increased starting number of Shells; reduced Attack recovery time

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Melinoë){#Prev}: reduced bonus Power per spent Shell now that the starting number is greater

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heinous Affront (Zeus x Ares){#Prev}: significantly increased how frequently this can affect foes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Premium Service (Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased power level while using {#AlertBoldFormat}Black Coat (Melinoë)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Success Rate (Hermes){#Prev}: removed {#AlertBoldFormat}Fig Leaf (Dionysus) {#Prev}as an offering requirement for this

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Dangers{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Typhon{#Prev}: reduced damage and frequency of some attacks; adjusted Life and Armor of some minions; improved camera motion between phases
      · {#Spoiler}Spawn of Typhon{#Prev}: reduced damage of some attacks; reduced range and speed of headbutt attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prometheus{#Prev}: reduced damage of some attacks; other minor changes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Aetos{#Prev}: slightly increased damage of fly-up attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Satyr Sapper{#Prev}: reduced damage of ranged attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Auto-Watcher{#Prev}: slightly reduced damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Auto-Seeker{#Prev}: reduced damage of ranged attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Blasket{#Prev}: reduced damage

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved feedback when gathering {#AlertBoldFormat}Blood Drops {#Prev}from {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Increased appearance rate of Poppy Seeds in {#AlertBoldFormat}Tartarus 
      · Updates and fixes to translations in some languages

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed certain effects not increasing {#AlertBoldFormat}Moonstone Axe {#Prev}Omega Special channeling speed as expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Black Coat {#Prev} Omega Attack having unintentionally reduced range in the previous patch
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Extended Family (Hera) {#Prev}not being affected by Boons from {#AlertBoldFormat}Artemis{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Athena{#Prev}, or  {#AlertBoldFormat}Dionysus
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Nova Flourish (Apollo) {#Prev}not increasing the area of the {#AlertBoldFormat}Moonstone Axe {#Prev}Omega Special
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Steady Growth (Demeter) {#Prev}sometimes not working correctly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Mint Condition (Hephaestus) {#Prev}not functioning in the newest Warden encounter in {#AlertBoldFormat}Thessaly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Gorgon Amulet (Athena) {#Prev}sometimes summoning multiple {#AlertBoldFormat}Athenas {#Prev}in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Mourning Fields
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Fig Leaf (Dionysus) {#Prev}not functioning in the newest Warden encounter in {#AlertBoldFormat}Thessaly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Hermes {#Prev}sometimes unexpectedly showing up as the first Olympian on the surface over and over after reaching the final confrontation
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several narrative events related to the final confrontation playing or not playing when expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed visual issues with the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes {#Prev}in ultrawide resolutions
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a visual issue with the numbering on the {#AlertBoldFormat}Death {#Prev}Arcana in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes
      · Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'Zeus now cast his new weapon, pale and blinding, through the fabric of the sky, ripping it end to end; then he hurled another, stronger, at his father: it fell like a white-hot sword thrust with inexorable force.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Greek Myths: A New Retelling {#QuoteBaseFormat}(C. Higgins)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0007"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 7: The WARSONG Update - February 19, 2025

      Our second {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}has arrived, featuring the final confrontation of the surface route, one last Olympian and all his Boons, a new Animal Familiar to bond with, streamlined resource gathering, plenty of new music and artwork, and more! We're excited to know what you think, and will be monitoring feedback in the coming weeks to ensure these latest additions are working properly.

      {#AlertH2Format}Highlights{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Final Confrontation{#Prev}: Battle to the summit of {#AlertBoldFormat}Mount Olympus {#Prev}and discover what awaits...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Olympian{#Prev}: Meet the god of war himself, and choose from his many Boons
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Familiar{#Prev}: Find one last animal companion to join your journey and aid you in battle
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Revamped Boons{#Prev}: Gain many powerful new and improved blessings from various Olympians
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Revamped Altar of Ashes{#Prev}: Activate several reworked effects, and each Card now has all-new artwork
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Revamped Resource Gathering{#Prev}: Worry no more about which resources you can collect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Revamped Menus{#Prev}: Look for new and improved animations across many menu screens
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Expanded Story{#Prev}: Discuss the final confrontation and more with many different characters

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      · You no longer prioritize {#AlertBoldFormat}Gathering Tools {#Prev}in the Training Grounds, though still can harvest any type of resource as long as you have unlocked each Tool; resource appearance rates adjusted as part of this
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Psyche {#Prev}can no longer be found as a Location Reward; {#AlertBoldFormat}Bones {#Prev}may now be found sooner instead
      · All Guardians and Wardens with Guardian-style Life Bars now are resistant to the slowing effect of your Casts; previously this applied only to some of them
      · Any damage resistance effects you have no longer affect any Armor you have
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Added a longer visual warning before taking damage from magma and fire effects
      · Adjusted requirements for certain key events early on; as a result, it should be possible to reach the surface earlier than before

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff{#Prev}: Attack sequence is faster and the final strike is stronger; Omega Attack is stronger; reworked Special is a fast powerful shot that pierces foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull{#Prev}: reworked Attack fires straight ahead; Omega Attack is stronger; Special now retrieves Shells in the surrounding area 
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Black Coat{#Prev}: increased Omega Attack damage; your Dash no longer cancels channeling your Omega Attack and causes you to perform the move right after

      {#AlertH2Format}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}
      · All Cards now have unique illustrations; swapped or adjusted themes of several Cards, noted below
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eternity{#Prev}: theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Night{#Prev}; reworked — now makes everything slower while you channel Omega moves; note this effect is no longer on {#AlertBoldFormat}Silver Wheel (Hecate){#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Messenger{#Prev}: reworked — your Casts briefly make you impervious and move faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Swift Runner{#Prev}: your Sprint now also makes you phase through foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Night{#Prev}: reduced Grasp cost; theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Death{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Wayward Son{#Prev}: no longer provides doubled recovery at low Life; base recovery improved
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Death{#Prev}: theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Eternity{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Persistence{#Prev}: theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}The Titan{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Enchantress{#Prev}: theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}The Fates{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Fates{#Prev}: theme changed from {#AlertBoldFormat}The Seer{#Prev}
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Grasp {#Prev}upgrade costs re-scaled as part of changes to resource gathering

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · Added new {#AlertBoldFormat}Testaments {#Prev}for the final confrontation
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Shadow{#Prev}: adjusted various encounters with this
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Fangs{#Prev}: removed certain combinations of Perks that were unusually cruel... 
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fear requirements for some Testaments re-scaled to reduce jumps in difficulty; reduced Fear requirements in some cases

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · Added {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ares{#Prev}, with many of his own blessings, including a new {#AlertBoldFormat}Duo {#Prev}with each other primary Boon-giver
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Zeus{#Prev}: his {#AlertBoldFormat}Blitz {#Prev}Curse now activates at the end of the duration if not activated by dealing damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Storm Ring (Zeus){#Prev}: slightly reduced rate of lightning strikes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Thunder Rush (Zeus){#Prev}: no longer requires Magick to strike foes with lightning; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Thunder Sprint
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Electric Overload (Zeus){#Prev}: reworked — your chain-lightning effects are stronger and bounce to more foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Toasting Fork (Zeus){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Arc Flash (Zeus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Moves activate your Blitz effects and make them stronger
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Romantic Spark (Zeus x Aphrodite){#Prev}: reduced damage bonus
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hera{#Prev}: the Queen of the Olympians now has Boons of all four elemental affinities, not solely Earth
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Engagement Ring (Hera){#Prev}: reworked — now deals immediate damage for each foe in the binding circle
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bridal Glow (Hera){#Prev}: reworked — upgrades a random Boon to Heroic Rarity and gives it bonus Pom Lv.
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nasty Comeback (Hera){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Extended Family (Hera){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Olympian damage is stronger for each Olympian you met this night
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Proper Upbringing (Hera){#Prev}: increased activation requirement to include all four elements
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Breaker Rush (Poseidon){#Prev}: reworked — whenever you Sprint, damage and knock away the first foe you run into; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Breaker Sprint
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Geyser Spout (Poseidon){#Prev}: reworked — your Omega Cast gains Power and knocks foes away
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Buried Treasure (Poseidon){#Prev}: now also drops {#AlertBoldFormat}Bones{#Prev}, not {#AlertBoldFormat}Ashes {#Prev}or {#AlertBoldFormat}Psyche{#Prev}; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Ocean's Bounty
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flood Control (Poseidon){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}High Surf (Poseidon){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Hit surrounding foes with a splash as they strike, but prime some Magick
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Phoenix Skin (Apollo x Hestia){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Warm Breeze (Apollo x Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever Dodge or Daze makes foes miss, restore some Life
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Demeter: {#Prev}her {#AlertBoldFormat}Gust {#Prev}effects no longer destroy trees in Erebus or other such obstructions
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Local Climate (Demeter){#Prev}: reworked — your Omega Cast is stronger; bonus doubled in the binding circle
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Plentiful Forage (Demeter){#Prev}: now restores Life whenever you gather any resource
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rare Crop (Demeter){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Steady Growth (Demeter){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you clear enough Encounters, a Boon gains Rarity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Secret Crush (Aphrodite){#Prev}: now also affects Omega Attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tough Gain (Hephaestus){#Prev}: reworked — whenever you take damage, shrug some off and restore Magick
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flash Fry (Hestia){#Prev}: no longer requires foes to have Scorch to explode when slain; no longer requires a Scorch-related Boon to be offered; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Natural Gas
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Burnt Offering (Hestia){#Prev}: reworked — gain max Magick whenever you collect Ashes, and gain some now
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mean Streak (Hermes){#Prev}: damage bonus no longer automatically ends after Encounters
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tall Order (Hermes){#Prev}: updated elemental requirement; slightly increased damage bonus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Travel Deal (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your first purchase each Location costs less Gold; another item appears after
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Saved Breath (Hermes){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Winner's Circle (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}You channel your Casts faster and your Casts expire faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witty Retort (Hermes){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hasty Retreat (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Gain more Dodge chance and move speed the more Boons you have
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Greater Evasion (Hermes){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Stutter Step (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}You can Dash more frequently
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Midnight Oil (Hermes){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Success Rate (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your chance-based effects are more likely to occur, except Dodge or Daze
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Close Call (Hermes){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Paid Dues (Hermes){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new Legendary! {#Prev}Whenever you take damage, you lose Gold before you lose Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mental Block (Athena){#Prev}: reduced duration of Impervious effect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Righteous Pike (Athena){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you use enough Magick, several foes are struck by spears
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Killing Stroke (Artemis){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials may deal Critical damage, but you prime some Magick
      · The {#AlertBoldFormat}Marked {#Prev}Curses inflicted by {#AlertBoldFormat}Artemis {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Raki the Raven {#Prev}now will never choose the same target
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Unseen Ire (Hades){#Prev}: the Dark effect and its damage bonus no longer expire after you strike
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Barren (Chaos){#Prev}: reduced Curse duration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Neurotic (Chaos){#Prev}: no longer slows your Dash but still makes it use Magick; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Hobbled
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Life Savings (Narcissus){#Prev}: now gives {#AlertBoldFormat}Lotus {#Prev}instead of {#AlertBoldFormat}Deathcaps
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wealth from the Dead (Medea){#Prev}: you now automatically absorb bonus Gold from slain foes on approach
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Supply Drop (Icarus){#Prev}: slightly reduced frequency of drops, and provides one fewer Pom Slice
      · Adjusted names and elemental affinities of some Boons
      · Additional minor adjustments to some bonuses from Rarity and {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · Further clarifications to descriptions for various Boons
      · Other minor fixes and adjustments

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spiral Knives (Blades){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hidden Knives (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Specials are stronger and Omega Special fires more shots than usual
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fetching Array (Skull){#Prev}: Shells now also automatically return faster; removed penalty to total Shells
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Looming Ignition (Skull){#Prev}: now also affects your Omega Attack; reaches full strength faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Possessed Array (Skull){#Prev}: increased Magick cost
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rocket Bombard (Skull){#Prev}: cut from game since this effect is now innate; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Boosted Ignition (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}After your Dash or Specials, your Attacks are faster and have bonus Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Counter Barrage{#Prev}: now launches more rockets, more often
      · Adjusted names and descriptive text for several Daedalus Hammer upgrades

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      · Added a new Keepsake now that {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares {#Prev}decided to show up, which you can gain in the customary way
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Silver Wheel (Hecate){#Prev}: reworked — adds to your Magick limit for the rest of the night
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fig Leaf (Dionysus){#Prev}: now can only affect one Encounter per Region, but still works if you unequip it
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Engraved Pin (Moros){#Prev}: now counts as a Death Defiance effect
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Evil Eye (Nemesis){#Prev}: now targets {#AlertBoldFormat}Prometheus {#Prev}if his Eagle {#AlertBoldFormat}Aetos {#Prev}is the one to vanquish you

      {#AlertH2Format}Animal Familiars{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Gale the Polecat{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Grants Dodge chance and move speed, blocks damage a few times per Region
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Toula the Cat{#Prev}: attacks more times successively; falls asleep faster {#AlertItalicFormat}(so she can wake back up faster!)

      {#AlertH2Format}Resources & Reagents{#Prev}
      · Added several new collectable resources found around the final confrontation
      · Removed {#AlertBoldFormat}Deathcaps {#Prev}from the game as part of broader changes to resources described further above

      {#AlertH2Format}Well of Charon{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Yarn of Ariadne{#Prev}: no longer consumed when meeting {#AlertBoldFormat}Hades{#Prev}, on whom this has no effect

      {#AlertH2Format}Shrine of Hermes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Fresh Sustenance MAX{#Prev}: reduced Life recovery
      · Reduced chance of offering Minor Finds over other types of items

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Dangers{#Prev}
      · Added a variety of foes for the final surface Region, including new Wardens and a new Guardian
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prometheus{#Prev}: adjusted behaviors; reduced damage for several moves; now sometimes foresees and dodges attacks, yet overall should be somewhat less punishing than before
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Aetos{#Prev}: reduced viciousness to some extent...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sky-Dracon{#Prev}: slightly reduced tracking speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Auto-Seeker{#Prev}: slightly reduced tracking speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eris{#Prev}: improved previews of her various attacks
      · {#Spoiler}The Yargonaut{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Warden added to the {#AlertBoldFormat}Rift of Thessaly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Charybdis{#Prev}: adjusted Tentacle behaviors; reduced overall difficulty
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Harpy Talon{#Prev}: slightly reduced radius of ranged attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Stickler{#Prev}: reduced damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Seesword{#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Blasket{#Prev}: reduced damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Infernal Beast{#Prev}: slightly increased Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Scylla{#Prev}: slightly increased Life
      · {#Spoiler}Hellifish{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Warden added to {#AlertBoldFormat}Oceanus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lurker{#Prev}: gained a defensive back-step maneuver after getting hit
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Headmistress Hecate{#Prev}: slightly increased Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Root-Stalker{#Prev}: adjusted behavior of tail; grew a second one
      · Various other minor changes to foes and combat encounters

      {#AlertH2Format}Special Encounters{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Reworked {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles {#Prev}combat encounters — vanquish specially-marked foes for a bounty in Gold
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Aetos {#Prev}will no longer swoop in to attack more than once prior to facing {#AlertBoldFormat}Prometheus
      · Slightly increased appearance rate of {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monuments {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Unseen Sigils {#Prev}on the surface
      · Slightly increased difficulty of {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monument {#Prev}foes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monuments {#Prev}no longer offer {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}rewards if your Hex is fully upgraded
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Athena {#Prev}more consistently vanquishes {#AlertBoldFormat}Revenants {#Prev}from the {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Return (Oath)
      · Minor adjustments to {#AlertBoldFormat}Artemis{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles{#Prev}, and {#AlertBoldFormat}Icarus {#Prev}appearance rates on the surface route
      · Two {#AlertBoldFormat}Arachne {#Prev}Cocoon encounters can no longer occur very close together in some cases
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Family Disputes{#Prev}, formerly called {#AlertBoldFormat}Trials of the Gods{#Prev}, now can include {#AlertBoldFormat}Ares{#Prev}; several Olympians put up more of a fight than before...

      {#AlertH2Format}Level Design & Environments{#Prev}
      · Added the final confrontation on the surface route and various new Locations within it
      · The {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus {#Prev}Region has one fewer Location to traverse before the Guardian
      · Encounters in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Rift of Thessaly {#Prev}that had too many waves {#AlertItalicFormat}(of foes) {#Prev}should now be more reasonable
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Optional rooms in {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra {#Prev}become more likely if you haven't found many that night
      · Reduced damage of Lone Shades freed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra Pylons
      · Resources can appear in more places in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra {#Prev}main square
      · Removed Bat Cage nearest to the initial entrance to the {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra {#Prev}main square
      · Added another Location that can randomly appear in {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus
      · Added another Location that can randomly appear in {#AlertBoldFormat}Oceanus
      · Added another Location that can randomly appear in {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra
      · The final battle prior to the Guardian of each of Region should no longer get replaced by Fountain chambers or character encounters
      · Adjusted resource points in some Locations, especially those close enough to exits that you could leave by accident while trying to harvest
      · Various minor fixes and improvements to various Locations

      {#AlertH2Format}Chaos Trials{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You now reappear before the {#AlertBoldFormat}Pitch-Black Stone {#Prev}upon returning from a Chaos Trial
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Thunder{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Zeus-themed Trial set in {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Glory{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Hera-themed Trial set on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of the Fall{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Demeter-themed Trial set in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Mourning Fields
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Slaughter{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Ares-themed Trial set in {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Destiny{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Chaos-themed Trial set on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Strife{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Eris-themed Trial set in {#AlertBoldFormat}Thessaly
      · Minor fixes and changes to several Trials

      {#AlertH2Format}The Crossroads Renewal Project{#Prev}
      · Updated Crossroads main grounds with new points of interest; the taverna now is easier to traverse
      · {#Spoiler}Artemis {#Prev}now sometimes provides musical accompaniment in the Crossroads
      · Added numerous new unlockable decorative items once the {#AlertBoldFormat}Renewal Project {#Prev}is available
      · Some decorative items now unlocked from a new spot in the taverna
      · Various forms of wildlife now may appear throughout the Crossroads
      · Some groups of Shades in the Crossroads now have captions when you Salute them
      · Recently-pacified Shades that appear in the Training Grounds now have varying appearances
      · Melinoë will sometimes cover up the family portrait in her tent after brooding too much
      · Odysseus will sometimes offer resources you may need; can sometimes be found seated in the taverna
      · Eris will no longer litter in the midst of conversation with others
      · The witch attendants of Hecate now are absent when she is
      · Improved presentation around plants that can be harvested in the Garden
      · Supply Shipments no longer prompt you to interact as frequently
      · The moon now shows different phases in the Training Grounds vista scene

      {#AlertH2Format}Crossroads Cauldron{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rage of the Elements{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you activate the statues on {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympus {#Prev}to defend you
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Path to Desired Blessings{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you track requirements for Boons listed in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows {#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Acceptance of Another Fate{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Salute the Oath of the Unseen to reset that night's random events
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shuffling of Noted Ballads{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets the {#AlertBoldFormat}Music Maker {#Prev}make music choices for you if you wish
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Deathly Fortune{#Prev}: now introduced later and no longer lets you exchange plants for {#AlertBoldFormat}Bones {#Prev}{#AlertItalicFormat}(only fish...)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Psychic Slivers of Clarity{#Prev}: removed from the game as part of resource system changes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bones of Arcane Wisdom{#Prev}: now makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Bones {#Prev}raise Magick limit rather than adding Armor; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Bones of Burnished Bronze

      {#AlertH2Format}Fated List of Minor Prophecies{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}The Arms of Night{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Rewards you for unlocking each of the Main Weapons
      · {#Spoiler}Master of War{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Rewards you for choosing various Boons of Ares
      · {#Spoiler}Storm in the Heavens{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Rewards you for prevailing on the surface route
      · {#Spoiler}Sword of the Night{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Rewards you for clearing the surface route with each Main Weapon
      · {#Spoiler}Power Beyond Legend{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Rewards you for choosing all Legendary Boons; these are no longer included with each Olympian's Boon prophecy

      {#AlertH2Format}Book of Shadows{#Prev}
      · Added new entries for various additions in this update
      · Updated relationship status display for relevant characters after the Incantation {#AlertBoldFormat}Empath's Intuition

      {#AlertH2Format}Menus & UI{#Prev}
      · Updated {#AlertBoldFormat}Main Menu {#Prev}to reflect this {#AlertBoldFormat}Major Update
      · Added art for all Arcana and adjusted layout in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes {#Prev}screen
      · Added animations for the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads Cauldron {#Prev}screen
      · Added animations for the {#AlertBoldFormat}Pitch-Black Stone {#Prev}screen
