      · Improved timing of Polyphemus knockout sequence
      · Minor improvements to Charybdis fight intro
      · Improved presentation choosing {#AlertBoldFormat}Boon Boon Boon (Echo)
      · Added several Commendation messages that may appear on the {#AlertBoldFormat}Victory Screen
      · Added more error messaging we hope no one will ever see
      · Updated {#AlertBoldFormat}Credits {#Prev}with several additional contributors
      · Updates and fixes to translations in all languages

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Rapture Ring (Aphrodite) {#Prev}not damaging foes at the edge of the binding circle
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monuments {#Prev}sometimes appearing unexpectedly if you had no {#AlertBoldFormat}Hex of Selene
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Icarus {#Prev}missing his targets unexpectedly {#AlertItalicFormat}(unless you're his father and expect disappointment)
      · Fixed optional rooms in {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra {#Prev}counting against Encounters needed to clear {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos {#Prev}Curses
      · Fixed unexpected delays prior to pre-fight dialogue against {#AlertBoldFormat}Hecate{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Polyphemus{#Prev}, and {#AlertBoldFormat}Eris
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Gameplay Timer not pausing in some instances while pacifying Lost Shades
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Moonstone Axe (Thanatos) {#Prev}full-charge sound re-playing when entering new Locations
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Nemesis {#Prev}sometimes getting stuck wandering the {#AlertBoldFormat}Mourning Fields
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Evil Eye (Nemesis) {#Prev}switching targets after clearing {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos Trials
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Dual Moonshot (Daedalus - Staff) {#Prev}sounds not playing for each shot
      · Fixed foes playing hurt sound effects when taking damage to their Armor rather than their Life
      · Many other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'All his fellow-immortals hate \[Ares\], from Zeus and Hera downwards, except Eris, and Aphrodite who nurses a perverse passion for him, and greedy Hades who welcomes the bold young fighting-men slain in cruel wars.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~The Greek Myths {#QuoteBaseFormat}(R. Graves)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0006"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 6 - October 24, 2024

      This patch includes targeted fixes and improvements we could make relatively soon after last week's big launch of the {#AlertHighlightFormat}Olympic Update{#Prev}. We're continuing to monitor your feedback as we look ahead toward what's next, as outlined in our {#AlertBoldFormat}Roadmap{#Prev}. Thank you for playing, and good luck with the climb!

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · You now can break Urns and other objects when you Sprint into them
      · Increased the attack range of Lone Shades, including ones trapped in {#AlertBoldFormat}Ephyra {#Prev}Pylons
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: Omega Special shots now pierce foes {#AlertItalicFormat}(excluding the Aspect of Pan's homing shots)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe{#Prev}: Omega Attack channels faster
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat{#Prev}: Omega Special locks on faster; works more reliably when used in quick succession

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Happy Haze ({#Spoiler}Dionysus{#Prev}){#Prev}: {#Spoiler}Festive Fog {#Prev}effect now also repeatedly stuns susceptible foes

      {#AlertH2Format}Pool of Purging{#Prev}
      · Reduced Gold value of Infusion Boons

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Dangers{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Prometheus{#Prev}: adjusted Flame Strike patterns; slightly reduced uppercut speed; kick and flurry not quite as punishing; improved visual clarity of some of his moves; he is now perhaps more fittingly Titan-sized...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eris{#Prev}: reduced number of phases; improved feedback on where she is aiming with some Rail attacks; reduced duration of her temporary damage bonus
      · {#Spoiler}Talos{#Prev}: slightly reduced Life
      · {#Spoiler}Mega-Dracon{#Prev}: slightly reduced Armor; fixed issues with it flying out of bounds
      · {#Spoiler}Auto-Watcher{#Prev}: reduced damage; reduced tracking speed; reduced Elite Armor
      · {#Spoiler}Snow-Shambler{#Prev}: reduced Life
      · {#Spoiler}Harpy Raptor{#Prev}: reduced Life
      · {#Spoiler}Satyr Sapper{#Prev}: reduced tracking speed; fewer should appear at once
      · {#Spoiler}Satyr Raider{#Prev}: reduced damage of some attacks
      · {#Spoiler}Satyr Goldpike{#Prev}: reduced damage of some attacks
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Charybdis{#Prev}: reduced tentacle damage; slightly reduced Life; slightly reduced frequency of ranged attacks
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Headmistress Hecate{#Prev}: her Twilight Curse can no longer be blocked using the {#Spoiler}Black Coat

      {#AlertH2Format}Special Encounters{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Significantly reduced how quickly {#AlertBoldFormat}Nemesis {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles {#Prev}sometimes snatch items from {#AlertBoldFormat}Charon
      · Reduced chances of not having any foes to drop in on when launching into {#Spoiler}Olympus {#Prev}Encounters

      {#AlertH2Format}Animal Familiars{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Raki the Raven{#Prev}: no longer has hidden damage bonuses against certain types of foe; fixed incorrect text for Marked effect duration, though the duration itself is unchanged
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Hecuba the Hound{#Prev}: no longer as prone to waiting around prior to digging

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Shadows{#Prev}: now affects {#AlertBoldFormat}Charybdis {#Prev}and {#Spoiler}Talos{#Prev}, so beware!

      {#AlertH2Format}Art & Visual FX{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved look and clarity of {#AlertBoldFormat}Harpy {#Prev}cyclone attack
      · Various other minor visual improvements

      {#AlertH2Format}Voice & Narrative{#Prev}
      · Adjusted how often {#AlertBoldFormat}Headmistress Hecate {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Chronos {#Prev}speak during battle
      · Adjusted priority and requirements for various voice lines and narrative events
      · Numerous other minor fixes and improvements

      {#AlertH2Format}Music & SFX{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis) {#Prev}sound not playing for the {#AlertBoldFormat}Riposte {#Prev}effect
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Adjusted some sound effects for {#Spoiler}Black Coat (Nyx){#Prev}, though these are still in progress
      · Adjusted some sound effects for {#AlertBoldFormat}Charybdis{#Prev}; improved music timing at the end of the fight
      · Adjusted sound effects when {#AlertBoldFormat}Eris {#Prev}gets dragged back to the Underworld
      · Improved blast sound for {#AlertBoldFormat}Beach Ball (Poseidon x Apollo)
      · Other minor fixes and improvements

      {#AlertH2Format}Menus & UI{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack The {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads Renewal {#Prev}menu now re-opens after unlocking new decorations
      · Added menu text for unlocking, swapping, and removing decorations
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack The {#AlertBoldFormat}Music Maker {#Prev}menu likewise now re-opens after unlocking new music

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack The {#AlertBoldFormat}Victory Screen {#Prev}now reveals your current Life if you have {#AlertBoldFormat}Worry Free ({#Spoiler}Dionysus{#Prev})
      · You now can interact with the exits in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Mourning Fields {#Prev}from farther away
      · Aspects of the {#Spoiler}Black Coat {#Prev}are no longer revealed immediately after you unlock the weapon
      · The moon beam surrounding the {#AlertBoldFormat}Pitch-Black Stone {#Prev}now dims if you have no uncleared {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos Trials
      · Added feedback when attempting to block unblockable attacks using the {#Spoiler}Black Coat
      · Improved collision near the exit from the {#AlertBoldFormat}Training Grounds {#Prev}back to the rest of the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads
      · Added more contextual hints for why various comrades may be uninterested in your various gifts
      · You now can re-map the commands when using the {#AlertBoldFormat}Tablet of Peace {#Prev}to compel Shades
      · Clarified descriptive text for several Boons
      · Various other minor text changes

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      · Fixed an issue with the {#AlertBoldFormat}Wretched Broker {#Prev}where you could keep using Sell All without selling all...
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Dora {#Prev}unexpectedly never showing up night after night despite claiming to enjoy the tent
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Silken Sash (Arachne) {#Prev}removing added Armor if you switched to a different Keepsake
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Shrine of Hermes expedited deliveries sometimes dropping out of bounds in the new Region
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Sureshot Flurry (Daedalus - Blades) {#Prev}not increasing Special range
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Furious Rockets (Daedalus - Coat) {#Prev}not increasing Omega Special speed
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Burnt Offering (Hestia) {#Prev}sometimes purging a different Boon than indicated
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Satyr Raider {#Prev}not taking damage from opposing {#Spoiler}Automatons{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Auto-Forcer {#Prev}damaging itself while afflicted with {#AlertBoldFormat}Charm
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Toula {#Prev}sliding around uncontrollably during the final confrontation with {#AlertBoldFormat}Chronos
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed reward in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Rift of Thessaly {#Prev}Fountain Chamber being unalterable
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several Boons not showing Offering Requirements in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows
      · Fixed exit sounds in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Rift of Thessaly {#Prev}and the new Region cutting off unexpectedly
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Music Maker {#Prev}music playing unexpectedly during the {#Spoiler}Hypnos dream sequence {#Prev}and while fishing
      · Fixed a visual issue in the destruction animation for {#Spoiler}Talos
      · Fixed various minor visual issues in some Locations
      · Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'There is no way of deceiving or evading the mind of Zeus, since not even Iapetos' son, sly Prometheus, escaped the weight of his wrath, and for all his cleverness a strong fetter holds him in check.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Theogony {#QuoteBaseFormat}(Hesiod; M.L. West translation)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0005"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 5: The OLYMPIC Update - October 16, 2024

      Our first {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}is finally here, featuring an all-new Region to explore, a new weapon to master, more characters to meet, new decorations for the Crossroads, new Animal Familiars to bond with, new music and artwork, and {#AlertItalicFormat}much {#Prev}more! We hope you enjoy discovering it all. In the coming weeks, we will be looking closely at player feedback to ensure our latest changes are solid. Until then!

      {#AlertH2Format}Highlights{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Region{#Prev}: Can you reach {#Spoiler}Olympus, the mountain of the gods{#Prev}? And if so... can you save it?
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Weapon{#Prev}: Wield the otherworldly might of {#Spoiler}Xinth, the Black Coat {#Prev}— last of the Nocturnal Arms
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Characters{#Prev}: Track down two new allies on their home turf and earn their favor
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}New Familiars{#Prev}: You now can bond with two new animal companions... once you find them!
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crossroads Renewal{#Prev}: Unlock dozens of new cosmetic items to liven up the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads {#Prev}your way
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Expanded Story{#Prev}: Discover hours of new dialogue, as the plot thickens once you reach the new Region
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}World Map{#Prev}: Look for this new presentation when moving from one Region of the world to another
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mac Support{#Prev}: The game now runs natively on Mac systems with Apple M1 or later

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff{#Prev}: reworked Special is faster and bounces between foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: reworked Special pierces foes and returns to you, potentially hitting foes more than once
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames{#Prev}: Special projectiles spin left or right depending on your movement
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe{#Prev}: reworked Special is a rising slash that strikes several times, but no longer blocks foes
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Guard and retaliate with mighty Attacks, ensuring none escape with seeking Specials
      · Your {#AlertBoldFormat}Dash {#Prev}is innately faster and more responsive
      · You now can more reliably Dash out of hit-stun effects from certain foes' strikes
      · It should be easier to aim certain abilities using gamepad

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Moros){#Prev}: re-scaled upgrades; slightly reduced fully-upgraded blast damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Medea){#Prev}: increased Attack & Special damage; improved upgrades; Shells now load faster
      · {#Spoiler}Black Coat{#Prev}: added its own three different unlockable, upgradeable Aspects

      {#AlertH2Format}Crossroads Cauldron{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eyes of Night and Darkness{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Monuments {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Unseen Sigils {#Prev}sometimes appear in Locations, further described below
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Earthly Fortune{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you recycle unneeded resources at the {#AlertBoldFormat}Wretched Broker{#Prev}, in exchange for {#AlertBoldFormat}Prestige{#Prev}, used for decorative items
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Summoning of Musical Rhapsody{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Required to summon the {#AlertBoldFormat}Music Maker{#Prev}, who lets you unlock different music to play in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spreading of Ashes{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you save multiple Arcana arrangements in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Favored of All Keepsakes{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you designate a Keepsake to auto-equip in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Training Grounds
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Abyssal Reflections{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets you re-attempt cleared {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos Trials{#Prev}, and tracks your fastest times
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bravery of Familiar Spirits{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Now required to upgrade your {#AlertBoldFormat}Animal Familiars
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Arisen Troves{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Infernal Troves {#Prev}sometimes appear in Surface Locations
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Surge of Desecrating Pools{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Makes {#AlertBoldFormat}Pools of Purging {#Prev}appear between Underworld Regions
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Frozen Lifespring{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Makes a Fountain Chamber sometimes appear in the new Region
      · Adjusted requirements and costs of several Incantations
      · Melinoë and Hecate now will sometimes conclude Incantations in unison

      {#AlertH2Format}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Sorceress{#Prev}: reworked — makes Omega moves faster; prior effect now on {#AlertBoldFormat}Silver Wheel (Hecate)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Swift Runner{#Prev}: no longer makes your Dash faster, since this effect now is innate
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Death{#Prev}: added a new UI indicator for the effect
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Strength{#Prev}: reworked; now provides a {#AlertItalicFormat}global {#Prev}damage boost, if you have no Death Defiance effects
      · Adjusted upgrade costs of various Cards
      · Improved contextual hints for upgrading {#AlertBoldFormat}Grasp
      · Clarified descriptive text for various Cards

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      · Each of the two new allies you can meet has a unique Keepsake you can gain in the customary way
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Silver Wheel (Hecate){#Prev}: reworked — now slows everything around you while you channel Omega moves
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gold Purse (Charon){#Prev}: now affected by Gold-boosting Boons such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Affluence (Chaos)
      · Improved feedback and fixes for when certain Keepsakes expire for the night
      · Adjusted placements of some Keepsakes in the Display Case {#AlertItalicFormat}(to make room for the new ones!)
      · Clarified descriptive text for several Keepsakes

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · Each of the two new allies you can meet has their own blessings to aid in your task
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}All Together (Hera){#Prev}: renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Elementary Particles{#Prev}; now her Legendary, no longer a Hestia Duo
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cherished Heirloom (Hera x Demeter){#Prev}: now also improves your current Keepsake, not just later ones
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spiteful Strength (Hera x Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game, though the effect can now be found in {#AlertBoldFormat}Wells of Charon {#Prev}in the new item {#AlertBoldFormat}Danaid Dagger
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Brave Face (Hera x Hephaestus){#Prev}: this is now a Duo and no longer offered by Hera alone
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Incandescent Aura (Hera x Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you restore Magick, damage surrounding foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Frosty Veneer{#Prev}: reduced effectiveness {#AlertItalicFormat}(the minimum damage you can take is now increased)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ocean's Bounty (Poseidon){#Prev}: Ash and Psyche rewards now are guaranteed; updated presentation
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Plentiful Forage (Demeter){#Prev}: reduced Life gain
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Snow Queen (Demeter){#Prev}: no longer blocks damage from {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Time (Oath)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Love Handles (Aphrodite x Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased effectiveness
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heart Breaker (Aphrodite){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}Heartthrobs {#Prev}now deal reduced damage and require more Magick to appear
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Smithy Sprint (Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Stamp Rush (Hephaestus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}After you Dash, occasionally create a blast around a nearby foe
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mint Condition (Hephaestus){#Prev}: reduced invulnerability duration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Grand Caldera (Hephaestus){#Prev}: fixed Heroic Rarity, which previously was not stronger than Epic
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crispy Coating (Hestia){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hot Pot (Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}You have a chance to Dodge damage, doubled against Scorch-afflicted foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cinerary Circle (Hades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you use enough Magick, summon Soul Urns around you that deal area damage when destroyed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Last Gasp (Hades){#Prev}: bonus damage slightly reduced though now scales with number of Death Defiance effects used that night, not just how many you have missing
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Pom Pom Pom (Echo){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Double the Pom Lv. of your Boon with the highest Pom Lv.
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Boon Boon Boon (Echo){#Prev}: now lets you choose one of three random Boons from the previous night
      · Adjusted names and descriptive text for several Boons
      · Other minor fixes and adjustments

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · Added all-new upgrades for the new weapon
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hook Knives (Blades){#Prev}: cut from game, since this effect now is innate; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Reaper Knives (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials have bonus Power and deal damage in a wider area
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Empowering Guard (Axe){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Siege Shredder (Axe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Special strikes farther ahead and deals bonus damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Advancing Whirlwind (Axe){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Seething Marauder (Axe){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Each of your Attacks also deals damage to surrounding foes
      · Adjusted names and descriptive text for several Daedalus Hammer upgrades

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes & Path of Stars{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Overflow{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}While using {#AlertBoldFormat}Lunar Ray{#Prev}, deal damage in an area around you
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Impact{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}{#AlertBoldFormat}Lunar Ray {#Prev}has bonus Power when it first deals damage each Encounter
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Saturation{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Using {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Water {#Prev}also fires your Omega Cast immediately
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Consequence{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever {#AlertBoldFormat}Total Eclipse {#Prev}strikes a guardian, your next use of it is partially charged
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Eminence{#Prev}: now a Sublime-quality upgrade for {#AlertBoldFormat}Total Eclipse{#Prev}, and incurs a Magick cost increase
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tenacity{#Prev}: now a Sublime-quality upgrade for {#AlertBoldFormat}Wolf Howl{#Prev}, and incurs a Magick cost increase
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Frenzy{#Prev}: now a Bright-quality upgrade for {#AlertBoldFormat}Wolf Howl{#Prev}, and no longer incurs a Magick cost increase
      · Adjusted several upgrades to use the condition {#AlertItalicFormat}After using your Hex this Encounter{#Prev}, instead of {#AlertItalicFormat}While your Hex is not ready
      · Clarified descriptive text for various Path of Stars upgrades

      {#AlertH2Format}Well of Charon{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Danaid Dagger{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attacks and Specials are stronger while not empowered by Boons; previously this effect was on the Boon {#AlertBoldFormat}Spiteful Strength (Hera x Hephaestus)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sacrificial Hymn{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Sacrifice Boons will be offered as soon as possible, and your next is stronger; previously this effect was on the Boon {#AlertBoldFormat}Family Trade (Hera)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mist Veil{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}After you use Magick, restore it rapidly up to a limit; previously this effect was on the Keepsake {#AlertBoldFormat}Silver Wheel (Hecate)
