      {#AlertH2Format}Special Encounters{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moon Monuments{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}These can appear after the Incantation {#AlertBoldFormat}Eyes of Night and Darkness{#Prev}, challenging you to vanquish a powerful Elite foe for a special reward
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Unseen Sigils{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}These can appear after the Incantation {#AlertBoldFormat}Eyes of Night and Darkness{#Prev}, challenging you to vanquish a group of foes without taking a hit for a special reward
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Reduced duration before {#AlertBoldFormat}Infernal Trove {#Prev}rewards may be collected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Nemesis {#Prev}will no longer appear in place of {#AlertBoldFormat}Echo {#Prev}after the first time; she is less quick about gruffly running through exits; she is less quick to purchase items from {#AlertBoldFormat}Charon
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Adjusted {#AlertBoldFormat}Heracles {#Prev}combat encounter intensity; his first victim no longer appears as often near Location entrances; he now exits sooner afterwards; he now can sometimes appear in the new Region
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Icarus {#Prev}is more effective against your common foes; he now can sometimes appear in the new Region
      · Boons of {#AlertBoldFormat}Hermes {#Prev}now may be offered among the options when you set forth each night
      · {#Spoiler}Chaos Gates {#Prev}may appear sooner than before on the Surface route after a certain point
      · Adjusted intensity of {#AlertBoldFormat}Trial of the Gods {#Prev}encounters on the Surface; no longer occur in smaller Locations

      {#AlertH2Format}Animal Familiars{#Prev}
