    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0004"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 4 - July 16, 2024
      This smaller patch addresses various issues we've observed since our previous patches, which we wanted to alleviate before our first {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}later this year. Thank you for your feedback and support!

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Melinoë){#Prev}: increased damage striking foes from behind

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lightning Lance (Zeus){#Prev}: improved targeting while using gamepad controls
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spirit Surge (Zeus){#Prev}: reworked; now whenever you use Magick, a surrounding foe is struck by lightning
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sworn Strike (Hera){#Prev}: slightly reduced bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Engagement Ring (Hera){#Prev}: reworked; inflicts Hitch on foes, and any slain in the circle deal area damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Family Trade (Hera){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rousing Reception (Hera){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Casts damage foes as they enter the Encounter, wherever they appear {#AlertItalicFormat}(this effect was previously innate to Engagement Ring)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Golden Rule (Hera x Poseidon){#Prev}: now applies a multiplicative global damage bonus, rather than a flat bonus only to Attacks and Specials
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Beach Ball (Poseidon x Apollo){#Prev}: added greater damage and area scaling over a brief charge-up duration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mint Condition (Hephaestus){#Prev}: invulnerability effect now resets between Encounters in the same Location

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mirrored Thrasher (Staff){#Prev}: removed Life penalty; now requires Magick instead
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Skulking Slice (Blades){#Prev}: reduced bonus damage striking foes from behind
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Escalating Ambush (Blades){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wicked Onslaught (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Adds power to Attacks
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Melting Shredder (Axe){#Prev}: increased damage to Armor
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Inverted Spark (Flames){#Prev}: now also causes projectiles to linger for longer
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Whirling Coil (Flames){#Prev}: projectiles no longer spin in place; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Origin Coil{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crushing Comet (Flames){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Triple Comet (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Special fires more projectiles
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Destructive Array (Skull){#Prev}: now deals a percentage of your Attack damage whenever your Shells drop
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rocket Bombard (Skull){#Prev}: increased damage

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes of Selene{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Phase Shift{#Prev}: rescaled some {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}upgrades
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lunar Ray{#Prev}: rescaled damage over a shorter duration

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Encounters{#Prev}
      · {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}: adjusted sequencing of some moves; now easier to strike from behind after certain moves
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Headmistress Hecate{#Prev}: now easier to strike from behind after certain moves

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Haunting{#Prev}: Revenants can no longer spawn others; you now collect them from farther away
      · Damage penalties from {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Blood {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Vow of Suffering {#Prev}now are added, rather than multiplied

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several later narrative events related to {#AlertBoldFormat}Nemesis {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Moros {#Prev}never playing
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interaction between {#AlertBoldFormat}Witch's Staff (Momus) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Mirrored Thrasher (Daedalus - Staff)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed visual shield from {#AlertBoldFormat}The Lovers (Arcana) {#Prev}not appearing while using {#AlertBoldFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed some hit-stun effects applying unexpectedly during {#AlertBoldFormat}Riposte {#Prev}from {#AlertBoldFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Ionic Gain (Zeus) {#Prev}not working correctly while {#Spoiler}Icarus {#Prev}is around
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Glorious Disaster (Zeus x Apollo) {#Prev}using Magick without activating the bonus effect
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Hail Storm (Zeus x Demeter) {#Prev}sometimes not working on {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interaction between {#AlertBoldFormat}Bridal Glow (Hera) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Heavy Metal (Hephaestus)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Hydraulic Might (Poseidon) {#Prev}unexpectedly granting invulnerability at the start of Encounters
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Water Fitness (Poseidon) {#Prev}unexpectedly restoring Life whenever you gained Water essences
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Freezer Burn (Demeter x Hestia) {#Prev}sometimes not working on {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Icarus {#Prev}Armor boosts not correctly adding to {#AlertBoldFormat}Hephaestus {#Prev}Armor boosts
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Burnt Offering (Hestia) {#Prev}sometimes selecting a different Boon to sacrifice if Rarified
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Hard Target (Hermes) {#Prev}not affecting {#AlertBoldFormat}Sea-Serpent {#Prev}shots and other splitting shots
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Atrophic ({#Spoiler}Chaos{#Prev}) {#Prev}sometimes displaying incorrect values
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Aetheric Moonburst (Daedalus - Staff) {#Prev}not restoring Magick when your Magick is full
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Inverted Spark (Daedalus - Flames) {#Prev}sometimes preventing Attacks from destroying urns
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interaction between {#AlertBoldFormat}Phase Shift (Selene) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Alacrity {#Prev}upgrade not resetting properly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Lunar Ray (Selene) {#Prev}firing indefinitely if you collected a reward while firing
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed interaction between {#AlertBoldFormat}Experimental Hammer ({#Spoiler}Icarus{#Prev}) {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Full Salvo (Daedalus - Skull){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several Keepsakes not correctly showing up as expired when switching between regions
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Headmistress Hecate {#Prev}shadow copies being vulnerable to Aphrodite's {#AlertBoldFormat}Charm {#Prev}Curse
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed upgraded {#AlertBoldFormat}Warding Circles {#Prev}in {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus {#Prev}sometimes recharging your Hex multiple times
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed instances where time-slow effects could unexpectedly persist if quickly chained together
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Guardians appearing to restore Life after taking heavy damage from Hestia's Scorch Curse
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed cases where using {#AlertBoldFormat}Change of Fate {#Prev}on a reward preview would not offer a different result
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Witch of the Crossroads {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Natural Talent {#Prev}Prophecies not appearing as expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Moon Beam (Selene) {#Prev}sometimes unexpectedly displaying as expired in Boon Info
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several Boons not appearing in their respective Olympians' Fated List Prophecies
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Breath of Eros (Charon) {#Prev}not appearing in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Valued Customer {#Prev}Fated List Prophecy
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a display issue in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Fated List {#Prev}with the prompt to view more requirements
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Reset option in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Oath of the Unseen {#Prev}not always resetting all Vows as expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed instances where camera motion could push Melinoë offscreen in the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed an issue preventing the use of the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows {#Prev}while {#Spoiler}Icarus {#Prev}is around
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed occasional visual issues with special deliveries from {#AlertBoldFormat}Shrines of Hermes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text and voiceover errors
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several rare crashes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'Ghost-evocation technology is first laid out in Homer's Odyssey and remains fairly conservative throughout ancient literature.{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Magic, Witchcraft, and Ghosts in the Greek and Roman Worlds {#QuoteBaseFormat}(D. Ogden)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0003"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 3 - June 26, 2024
      This patch improves numerous Olympian Boons to further enhance core combat and related choices. It also adds new UI icons, Cauldron Incantations, and more. Though we'll continue monitoring your feedback, we're now focusing on our first {#AlertHighlightFormat}Major Update {#Prev}slated for later this year. Thank you for playing!

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Many {#AlertBoldFormat}Duo Boons {#Prev}and some {#AlertBoldFormat}Legendary Boons {#Prev}should be offered more frequently
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Charon's Gold Rewards {#Prev}now include {#AlertBoldFormat}Nightmare {#Prev}after a certain point
      · Reworked {#AlertBoldFormat}Gathering Tool {#Prev}upgrades; now let you find +1 Elemental Essence for your {#AlertBoldFormat}Infusion Boons
      · Entering {#Spoiler}Chaos {#Prev}while in the {#Spoiler}Mourning Fields {#Prev}no longer causes you to skip a Location in that region
      · Slightly increased the minimum number of Boons and similar rewards you can find past {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus
      · Warding Circles in {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus {#Prev}now stagger foes that touch them

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Circe){#Prev}: indirect damage from Omega Moves now contributes to activating Serenity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis){#Prev}: you now are immune to hit-stun effects during Riposte
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Eos){#Prev}: improved Omega Attack tracking, though slightly increased Magick cost and reduced max damage from upgrade path; Attack sequence now continues after using it
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Persephone){#Prev}: now any Cast damage {#AlertItalicFormat}(not just Omega Cast) {#Prev}extends your Omega Special

      {#AlertH2Format}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}
      · Rearranged {#AlertBoldFormat}Grasp {#Prev}costs and positions of several Cards; you may need to reset your Arcana loadout
      · Swapped the names and theming of {#AlertBoldFormat}The Moon {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Night
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Death{#Prev}: reworked; Omega moves have a chance to deal Critical damage if the last one used was different
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Moon{#Prev}: now costs 0 Grasp but has an Awakening requirement to activate any surrounding Card
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Unseen{#Prev}: improved Magick restoration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Divinity{#Prev}: Awakening requirement expanded to include activating a column of Cards {#AlertItalicFormat}(not just a row)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Origination{#Prev}: now specifies that Curses from different Olympians are required; this is relevant with Demeter, whose Cyclone now is considered a Curse {#AlertItalicFormat}(along with her Freeze)

      {#AlertH2Format}Crossroads Cauldron{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Temporal Fluctuation{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Lets time-slow effects such as {#AlertBoldFormat}Phase Shift (Selene) {#Prev}work vs. {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Circles of the Moon{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Activating Warding Circles in Erebus fully charges your Hex
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ashen Memories of Life{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you claim rewards of Ash, slightly raise your Life limit
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Psychic Slivers of Clarity{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you claim rewards of Psyche, slightly raise your Magick limit
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bones of Burnished Bronze{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you claim rewards of Bones, gain some Armor
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nectar of Godly Savor{#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Whenever you claim rewards of Nectar, gain +1 Lv. for a random Boon

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}White Antler (Artemis){#Prev}: reworked; now provides Critical bonus for one Region, but reduces Life limit
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Silken Sash (Arachne){#Prev}: you no longer lose your Armor from this if you switch to a different Keepsake
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moon Beam (Selene){#Prev}: now also causes {#AlertBoldFormat}Selene {#Prev}or a {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}to be offered soon
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Olympian Keepsakes {#Prev}are now even more likely to make their respective Olympian Boons appear

      {#AlertH2Format}Boons & Blessings{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heaven Strike (Zeus){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Heaven Flourish (Zeus){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Storm Ring (Zeus){#Prev}: now deals damage from all Casts {#AlertItalicFormat}(not just Omega Cast)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ionic Gain (Zeus){#Prev}: reworked; now spawns an {#AlertBoldFormat}Aether Font {#Prev}nearby that fully restores Magick when used
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Spirit Surge (Zeus){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Double Strike (Zeus){#Prev}: increased effect chance and bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms{#Prev}; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Second Strike{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shocking Loss (Zeus){#Prev}: increased effect chance; now activates when foes first take damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Glorious Disaster (Zeus x Apollo){#Prev}: reduced damage; fixed Magick not deducting correctly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Apocalyptic Storm (Zeus x Demeter){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hail Storm (Zeus x Demeter){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Freeze effects also cause lightning bolts to strike afflicted foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Master Conductor (Zeus x Hephaestus){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Hera{#Prev}: Slaying a foe now can afflict them with the {#AlertBoldFormat}Hitch {#Prev}Curse and spread that damage accordingly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sworn Strike (Hera){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sworn Flourish (Hera){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Engagement Ring (Hera){#Prev}: now also inflicts Hitch when dealing damage, though reduced direct damage to compensate; no longer increases Cast duration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nexus Sprint (Hera){#Prev}: now damages and inflicts Hitch on unafflicted foes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Born Gain (Hera){#Prev}: increased Primed Magick cost
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Keen Intuition (Hera){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Blood Line (Hera){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Moves also create a damaging rift for an added Magick cost
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Bridal Glow (Hera){#Prev}: Boons that are already Heroic can no longer be chosen for this
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Soul Mate (Hera x Aphrodite){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ecstatic Obsession (Hera x Aphrodite){#Prev}: one foe always has Charm {#AlertItalicFormat}(formerly Aphrodite's Legendary)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Cherished Heirloom (Hera x Demeter){#Prev}: increased power level when upgrading max-rank Keepsakes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Funeral Pyre (Hera x Hestia){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Elementary Particles (Hera x Hestia){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Gain +1 each Elemental Essence and an Infusion Boon for it
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wave Strike (Poseidon){#Prev}: increased bonus from {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tidal Ring (Poseidon){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Casts also immediately hit foes in front of you with a splash
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Geyser Spout (Poseidon){#Prev}: now a second-tier Cast Boon; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Geyser Ring
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Crashing Wave (Poseidon){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Splash Fount (Poseidon){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Omega Moves also create a watery blast near the first damaged foe
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Ocean's Bounty (Poseidon){#Prev}: merged with {#AlertBoldFormat}Sunken Treasure{#Prev}, which was removed as a stand-alone Boon
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Water Fitness (Poseidon){#Prev}: effect now scales with each Water Essence
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}King Tide (Poseidon){#Prev}: increased size bonus and damage bonus
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Beach Ball (Poseidon x Apollo){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Natural Selection (Poseidon x Demeter){#Prev}: increased chance of improved Rarity
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Scalding Vapor (Poseidon x Hestia){#Prev}: increased damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Nova Strike (Apollo){#Prev}: increased bonus from Rarity and {#AlertBoldFormat}Poms of Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Solar Ring (Apollo){#Prev}: reworked; now inflicts Daze and deals a burst of damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Prominence Flare (Apollo){#Prev}: now a second-tier Cast Boon; renamed from the earlier {#AlertBoldFormat}Solar Ring
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lucid Gain (Apollo){#Prev}: reworked; now restores Magick if you are standing in your Casts when they expire
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Perfect Image (Apollo){#Prev}: reworked; damage bonus now resets if you avoid taking damage for a duration
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Torrential Downpour (Apollo x Demeter){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Boreal Gust (Apollo x Demeter){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}While standing in Cyclones, you randomly fire damaging gales
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Stellar Slam (Apollo x Hephaestus){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rude Awakening (Apollo x Hephaestus){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Hephaestus blasts clear Daze and deal more damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Tranquil Gain (Demeter){#Prev}: now restores Magick based on a percentage of your current total
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Gale Force (Demeter){#Prev}: your Cast's Cyclone now can follow you if you also have {#AlertBoldFormat}Local Climate
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Frosty Veneer (Demeter){#Prev}: now scales with Water Essence rather than Earth; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Coarse Grit
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Freezer Burn (Demeter x Hestia){#Prev}: reworked; inflicting Freeze on a foe with Scorch deals damage and removes Scorch
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Aphrodite{#Prev}: increased power and duration of her Weak Curse
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rapture Ring (Aphrodite){#Prev}: now deals damage as it drags foes in
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Passion Rush (Aphrodite){#Prev}: reworked; now deals damage when you press Dash and again when you stop pressing Dash; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Passion Dash
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Glamour Gain (Aphrodite){#Prev}: now makes all nearby foes Weak, rather than one randomly
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shameless Attitude (Aphrodite){#Prev}: reworked; the damage bonus doubles if you haven't lost much Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wispy Wiles (Aphrodite){#Prev}: effect now scales with each Air Essence
      · {#AlertBoldFormat}Heartthrobs {#Prev}from {#AlertBoldFormat}Aphrodite {#Prev}now spawn behind Melinoë and no longer detonate on obstacles
