      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed control mapping overlap between Rarify and Offerings commands on the Boon Choice menu
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed discrepancies in how seconds and milliseconds displayed in certain timers
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed background artwork appearing unexpectedly during Fishing Pier scenes in the Crossroads
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Rod of Fishing indicator sometimes remaining visible after you miss your mark
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Olympian portrait positions if you spurned them and fail in a {#AlertBoldFormat}Trial of the Gods {#Prev}encounter
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Reagent Sensing (Cauldron) {#Prev}not detecting {#AlertBoldFormat}Darkness
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed cases where Melinoë did not appear to switch weapons as expected in the Training Grounds
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed an issue where you could senselessly squander your Rarify effect on the Spare Wealth offering
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed text overlap issue when a Hex's recharge cost was reduced
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed further miscellaneous issues when playing in ultrawide resolutions
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text and voiceover errors
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed various rare crashes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'Late Classical writers identify Artemis and Hecate to some degree with the moon, but it is not certain how ancient this connection is.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Crowell's Handbook of Classical Mythology {#QuoteBaseFormat}(E. Tripp)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0002"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 2 - June 4, 2024
      Among the improvements in this patch, look for many new UI icons as well as weapon-related balance changes aimed at enhancing core combat and related choices. Your feedback and volunteered gameplay data help inspire our changes, so thank you for playing! Stay tuned for Boon updates in our next patch.

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      · You now can encounter up to one additional Olympian each night {#AlertItalicFormat}(as in the previous game)
      · You now are likely to find one more Boon or other major reward while in {#AlertBoldFormat}Erebus
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Increased invulnerability duration after your {#AlertBoldFormat}Death Defiance {#Prev}effects activate
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved rewards of {#AlertBoldFormat}Ash {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Psyche {#Prev}can now be found in {#Spoiler}Oceanus {#Prev}and the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You now can press-and-hold to harvest repeatedly from {#AlertBoldFormat}Crescent Pick {#Prev}Outcroppings
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Toula {#Prev}should now stay closer to you in Encounters, especially in the {#Spoiler}Fields of Mourning{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Nemesis {#Prev}no longer offers {#AlertBoldFormat}Death Defiance {#Prev}items if you do not need to refill the effect
      · Reduced Gold cost of {#AlertBoldFormat}Selene's Boon {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}in {#AlertBoldFormat}Charon's Shop
      · Minor adjustments to the order in which Olympians may first appear early on
      · Normalized chances of finding {#AlertBoldFormat}Fishing Points {#Prev}in various regions

      {#AlertH2Format}Nocturnal Arms & Abilities{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff{#Prev}: Special knocks foes away, but is slightly slower; Omega Special is faster
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades{#Prev}: Special staggers standard foes longer; Attack visual FX better match the hitbox
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames{#Prev}: Attacks are stronger and faster; Omega Attack channels faster and uses less Magick; Special now gives a speed boost, but has reduced damage; Omega Special can be channeled while moving
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe{#Prev}: reworked Special provides a lingering barrier; Omega Attack channels slightly faster; Omega Special channels faster
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull{#Prev}: Omega Attack channels faster and hits a larger area

      {#AlertH2Format}Aspects of the Nocturnal Arms{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Circe){#Prev}: adjusted activation and duration of Serenity effect; Serenity now adds Omega bonus damage that scales with this Aspect's rank
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Witch's Staff (Momus){#Prev}: reworked; each of your Omega Moves automatically fires several times in succession from where you use them
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sister Blades (Artemis){#Prev}: you will Block again if the effect recharges while you are channeling; Block now takes priority over Dodge and similar effects
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Umbral Flames (Eos){#Prev}: reworked; Omega Attack now fires a slow shot that occasionally creates damage blasts and also copies your Specials
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe (Melinoë){#Prev}: reworked; now adds Power and max Life
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moonstone Axe (Thanatos){#Prev}: reworked; faster Attack adds Critical chance to Omega moves
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Medea){#Prev}: improved hit detection on foes near impassable obstacles
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Argent Skull (Persephone){#Prev}: you now earn Glory much faster, but only by using your Omega Cast; improved control responsiveness during Omega Special

      {#AlertH2Format}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moon Beam (Selene){#Prev}: increased bonus to {#AlertBoldFormat}Path of Stars {#Prev}upgrades

      {#AlertH2Format}Daedalus Hammer Upgrades{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Marauder Wallop (Staff){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rapid Thrasher (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}All your Attacks become faster
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Double Wallop (Staff){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wicked Thrasher (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}All your Attacks gain bonus Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Double Cataclysm (Staff){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mirrored Thrasher (Staff){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}All your Attacks hit twice, but you take more damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rapid Moonshot (Staff){#Prev}: also affects Omega Special
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Dual Moonshot (Staff){#Prev}: also affects Omega Special; reduced range; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Double Moonshot
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Shimmering Moonshot (Staff){#Prev}: also affects Omega Special
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Aetheric Moonburst (Staff){#Prev}: increased Magick restoration from Power Shots
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Concentrated Flurry (Blades){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Melting Dart (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Special destroys a large percentage of a foe's Armor
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Flick Knives (Blades){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Dash-Strike also fires several Special knives in a fan pattern
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rapid Onslaught (Blades){#Prev}: reworked to also affect Omega Attack; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Marauder Slice
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hook Knives (Blades){#Prev}: removed damage bonus; slightly reduced speed of knives returning to you
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Furious Fire (Flames){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mega Spark (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}All your Attacks travel farther and deal more damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Inverted Spark (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Dash to make shots from your Attacks reverse direction and hit foes again
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Leaden Spark (Flames){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Attacks knock foes away and have bonus Power
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sustained Spark (Flames){#Prev}: also increases move speed, instead of reducing; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Sustained Fire
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Melting Coil (Flames){#Prev}: no longer fires straight; also affects Omega Special; formerly {#AlertBoldFormat}Melting Comet
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Origin Coil (Flames){#Prev}: also affects Special
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Rapid Slash (Axe){#Prev}: reworked to also affect Omega Attack; renamed from {#AlertBoldFormat}Marauder Slash
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Giga Cleaver (Axe){#Prev}: removed two-stage channeling {#AlertItalicFormat}(it always double-fires but uses more Magick)
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Dashing Heave (Axe){#Prev}: removed damage bonus; instead, it now hits twice
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Sidelong Crash (Skull){#Prev}: cut from game; replaced with...
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mega Driver (Skull){#Prev}: {#AlertBoldFormat}new! {#Prev}Your Specials travel farther and deal more damage
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Colossus Driver (Skull){#Prev}: also affects Omega Special

      {#AlertH2Format}Hexes of Selene{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Wolf Howl{#Prev}: reduced Magick-spend requirement
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Twilight Curse{#Prev}: greatly reduced Magick-spend requirement; reduced foes afflicted; reduced cast time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Night Bloom{#Prev}: reduced Magick-spend requirement, effect duration, bonus damage, and cast time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lunar Ray{#Prev}: greatly reduced Magick-spend requirement; reduced damage; reduced cast time
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Moon Water{#Prev}: slightly increased Magick-spend requirement; slightly reduced healing
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Dark Side{#Prev}: slightly increased Magick-spend requirement; slightly reduced cast time

      {#AlertH2Format}Foes & Encounters{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}: various fixes and adjustments; there should be fewer cases where he's patently unfair
      · {#Spoiler}Infernal Cerberus{#Prev}: minor adjustments to some attack patterns in the first phase
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Eris{#Prev}: grenade attacks no longer wildly bounce around
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Polyphemus{#Prev}: reduced effectiveness of {#Spoiler}Mutant Sheep{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Goldwrath{#Prev}: reduced accuracy and tracking of beam attack
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Queen Lamia{#Prev}: slightly increased Armor; increased speed; other minor changes
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Reed-Stalker{#Prev}: increased projectile speed and target distance; reduced rotation speed
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Mourner{#Prev}: slightly increased rotation speed; slightly increased speed while attacking
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Lamia{#Prev}: slightly increased life and Elite armor
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Dire Shambler{#Prev}: reduced tracking speed between attacks
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hippo{#Prev}: self-destruct area should more closely match the visuals 

      {#AlertH2Format}Level Design & Environments{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Driftwood {#Prev}resources are more common in the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly {#Prev}{#AlertItalicFormat}(a further increase since last patch)
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Burning Oil Slicks in the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly {#Prev}will extinguish after Encounters, though may be reignited
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Adjusted Oil Slicks in some locations in the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly{#Prev}
      · Minor fixes to several locations

      {#AlertH2Format}Fated List of Minor Prophecies{#Prev}
      · Clearing {#AlertBoldFormat}Original Sins {#Prev}no longer requires choosing the very rare {#AlertBoldFormat}Barren {#Prev}curse from {#Spoiler}Chaos{#Prev}

      {#AlertH2Format}Chaos Trials{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Heartache{#Prev}: reduced difficulty and adjusted based on Aspect changes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}Trial of Haste{#Prev}: reduced difficulty and adjusted based on Aspect changes

      {#AlertH2Format}Oath of the Unseen{#Prev}
      · {#AlertHighlightFormat}Vow of Forsaking{#Prev}: no longer helps ensure you quickly get Duo and Legendary Boons

      {#AlertH2Format}Menus & UI{#Prev}
      · Added many new UI icons for {#AlertBoldFormat}Keepsakes{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Weapons{#Prev}, {#AlertBoldFormat}Well of Charon {#Prev}offerings, and more
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertBoldFormat}Insight Into Offerings (Cauldron) {#Prev}now also lets you check each Olympian's list of offerings in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows {#Prev}while choosing their Boons {#AlertItalicFormat}(or the equivalent with other characters)
      · {#Prev}With the prior change, adjusted default key binding for {#AlertBoldFormat}Rarify{#Prev}; some custom bindings have been reset
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Added a warning when you are down to your last use of {#AlertBoldFormat}Death Defiance
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Opening the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows {#Prev}should show entries for nearby characters more reliably
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Removed the Unused Grasp notification when exiting the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes {#Prev}while at a high Grasp limit
      · Updated {#AlertBoldFormat}Pitch-Black Stone {#Prev}screen to use Aspect-specific icons
      · Adjusted input action bar layout at the bottom of the Boon Screen and similar
      · Added borders to icons for Selene Hexes on the {#AlertBoldFormat}Gifts of the Moon {#Prev}screen
      · Added informational pop-up when using {#AlertBoldFormat}F10 {#Prev}to report bugs
      · Other minor changes

      {#AlertH2Format}Art & Visual FX{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Reduced some full-screen flashing or strobing, such as from time-slow effects

      {#AlertH2Format}Music & SFX{#Prev}
      · Added SFX for when certain active abilities such as Serenity are ready to use
      · Updated placeholder SFX for various {#AlertBoldFormat}Keepsakes{#Prev}
      · Updated SFX for projectile collisions with {#AlertBoldFormat}Umbral Flames (Moros){#Prev}

      {#AlertH2Format}Voice & Narrative{#Prev}
      · Unique voice lines should play more reliably when certain incantations are revealed in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Cauldron{#Prev}
      · Added voice lines when using {#AlertBoldFormat}Phase Shift (Selene) {#Prev}vs. {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}{#AlertItalicFormat}(or trying to...)
      · More voice lines should play when confiding in {#AlertBoldFormat}Frinos {#Prev}in certain contexts

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack While brooding over the family portrait in the Crossroads, you may now snap out of it sooner
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You now can fully control the game using keyboard only if you rebind Attack and Special
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack All timers now pause while in the presence of {#AlertBoldFormat}Charon
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack An {#AlertBoldFormat}Anvil of Fates {#Prev}will no longer be offered in {#Spoiler}Tartarus {#Prev}if you have not found a {#AlertBoldFormat}Daedalus Hammer
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack In the {#Spoiler}Hades {#Prev}Flashback, adjusted timing of hint for players who don't realize they are in control
      · Reduced requirements for the incantation {#AlertBoldFormat}Power to Pause and Reflect {#Prev}to be revealed
      · Melinoë now respawns in the center of her Magick Circle near her tent {#AlertItalicFormat}(she was a bit off before...)
      · Improved compatibility with more types of controllers
      · Updated text for various upgrades and abilities

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Double Up (Poseidon) {#Prev}sometimes doubling Mystery Boons; clarified description
      · Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Nightmare {#Prev}resources dropping unexpectedly in {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos Trials{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Omega moves occasionally becoming unresponsive after being chomped on by {#Spoiler}Polyphemus{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed deadliest attack of {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}occasionally hitting even if Melinoë was in a supposedly safe point
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Umbral Flames {#Prev}Attack preventing Magick regeneration before channeling Omega Attack
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}The Queen {#Prev}and {#AlertBoldFormat}Judgment (Arcana) {#Prev}appearing active while no others Arcana are active
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Hearth Gain (Hestia) {#Prev}no longer restoring Magick if chosen as a Sacrifice Boon
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed certain later {#AlertBoldFormat}Oath Testaments {#Prev}for the {#AlertBoldFormat}Sister Blades {#Prev}sometimes not appearing as expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed cases where you could go out of bounds using the {#AlertBoldFormat}Argent Skull {#Prev}in the battle vs. {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed more cases of some visual FX vs. {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}lingering between phases or after the fight
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Toula {#Prev}unceremoniously vanishing after you vanquish {#Spoiler}Chronos{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed additional issues with {#AlertBoldFormat}Sun Worshiper (Apollo){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed additional issues with {#AlertBoldFormat}Dark Side (Selene){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed additional issues with {#AlertBoldFormat}Twilight Curse (Selene){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a visual issue where {#Spoiler}Headmistress Hecate {#Prev}could appear to slide after snared by your Cast
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Spark of Ixion (Charon) {#Prev}causing a {#Spoiler}Chaos Gate {#Prev}to appear in {#Spoiler}Asphodel?{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Golden Boughs {#Prev}sometimes not marking all available rewards in the {#Spoiler}Fields of Mourning{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several narrative events that could play out of sequence
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Odysseus {#Prev}rather rudely walking away while in conversation with {#AlertBoldFormat}Nemesis{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Heracles {#Prev}sometimes leaping away {#AlertItalicFormat}forever
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Melinoë's voice pitch reverting during her return sequence despite certain {#Spoiler}Circe {#Prev}enchantments
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed incorrect {#Spoiler}Echo {#Prev}portrait in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows 
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed incorrect music playing in some {#AlertBoldFormat}Chaos Trials{#Prev}, or not playing as intended in some instances
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed rare cases of a looping sound playing indefinitely
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a rare instance when objectives in the Training Grounds could overlap
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several minor issues on the Victory Screen that shows when you prevail
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed additional miscellaneous issues when playing in ultrawide resolutions
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a rare crash in which the effect of {#AlertBoldFormat}Winter Harvest (Demeter) {#Prev}could repeat {#AlertItalicFormat}forever
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed various other rare crashes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text errors
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'Hecate was the Goddess of the Dark of the Moon, the black nights when the moon is hidden. She was associated with deeds of darkness, the Goddess of the Crossways, which were held to be ghostly places of evil magic.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~Mythology: Timeless Tales of Gods and Heroes {#QuoteBaseFormat}(E. Hamilton)
      """
    }
    {
      Id = "MainMenuScreen_PatchNotes_0001"
      OverwriteLocalization = true
      Description = """
      {#AlertHeaderFormat}Early Access Patch 1 - May 16, 2024
      Welcome to {#AlertHighlightFormat}Hades II Early Access{#Prev}!! We're very grateful for all the feedback so far, which inspired the targeted improvements and fixes in this first patch. Next, we'll be working on a patch with balance changes and additional improvements based on what we've observed. Thank you for playing!

      {#AlertH2Format}General Gameplay{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Your {#AlertBoldFormat}Sprint {#Prev}is innately faster and turning is more responsive; re-scaled abilities that boost this
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You now can {#AlertBoldFormat}Dash {#Prev}out of many attack recovery animations more reliably
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You now can gather from {#AlertItalicFormat}any {#Prev}resource point once you have unlocked the corresponding {#AlertBoldFormat}Gathering Tool{#Prev}; you now can {#AlertItalicFormat}Prioritize {#Prev}any available Tool in the Training Grounds to make its resources appear as often as before, while resources for Tools you do {#AlertItalicFormat}not {#Prev}Prioritize will appear far less often

      {#AlertH2Format}Altar of Ashes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#AlertHighlightFormat}The Swift Runner{#Prev}: now also makes your Dash immediate (note the faster speed means you are invulnerable for very slightly less time); re-scaled Sprint speed bonus since Sprint is innately faster now

      {#AlertH2Format}Level Design & Environments{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack It is easier to Dash across chasms in {#Spoiler}Oceanus{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack {#Spoiler}Driftwood {#Prev}resources are more common in the {#Spoiler}Rift of Thessaly{#Prev}

      {#AlertH2Format}Menus & UI{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Using a {#AlertBoldFormat}Well of Charon {#Prev}displays your current {#AlertBoldFormat}Gold {#Prev}without the need to check your {#AlertBoldFormat}Boon Info
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack The {#AlertBoldFormat}Grasp {#Prev}Upgrade Tutorial in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Altar of Ashes {#Prev}will repeat if ignored
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Added {#AlertBoldFormat}Patch Notes {#Prev}option to the Main Menu {#AlertItalicFormat}(where you can read this!)

      {#AlertH2Format}Miscellaneous{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Early encounters with {#Spoiler}Eris {#Prev}are less likely to occur; she also drops something of value...
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Related, if this already occurred, look for a one-time bonus in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads {#Prev}while {#Spoiler}Eris {#Prev}is present
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Entries in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Book of Shadows {#Prev}are generally easier to reveal
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack You can gift {#Spoiler}Echo {#Prev}without having to wait around as long after conversing
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Adjusted {#Spoiler}Animal Familiar {#Prev}upgrades invalidated by the {#AlertBoldFormat}Gathering Tool {#Prev}changes above
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack In the {#Spoiler}Hades {#Prev}Flashback, a hint will eventually play for players who don't realize they are in control
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved mouse selection in various cases
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Improved support for some additional controllers
      · Abilities that boost Sprint speed display more-accurate numbers {#AlertItalicFormat}(generally lower than before)
      · Updates and fixes to translations in some languages

      {#AlertH2Format}Bug Fixes{#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several issues with {#AlertBoldFormat}Dark Side (Selene){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Sun Worshiper (Apollo) {#Prev}sometimes preventing new foes from spawning 
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Fire Extinguisher (Hestia) {#Prev}not dealing damage as expected
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#AlertBoldFormat}Sister Blades Omega Attack {#Prev}not hitting {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}reliably from certain angles
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed {#Spoiler}Satyr Hoplites {#Prev}retaining the ability to block while afflicted with {#AlertBoldFormat}Twilight Curse (Selene){#Prev}
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed various cases of foes sometimes spawning out of bounds
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed camera zoom-in getting stuck vs. {#Spoiler}Polyphemus {#Prev}in certain situations
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed cases where you could Dash out of bounds in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed Fishing Pier events in the {#AlertBoldFormat}Crossroads {#Prev}not passing Whiles like other similar events
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed autolock not clearing as expected while using mouse controls
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed keyboard inputs sometimes getting stuck unexpectedly
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several input issues switching from gamepad to mouse-and-keyboard controls
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several issues playing in ultrawide resolutions
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed some visual FX vs. {#Spoiler}Chronos {#Prev}lingering between phases or after the fight
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed a Melinoë voice line repeating unexpectedly around the {#Spoiler}City of Ephyra Bat Cages
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed various rare crashes
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Fixed several text errors
      @GUI\\Icons\\GhostPack Other minor fixes

      {#QuoteH2Format}Quote of the Patch{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}'...now plain to the eye, now shadowy, now shining in the darkness—{#Prev}
      {#QuoteItalicFormat}all this in unnerving attacks in the gloom of night.'{#Prev}

      {#QuoteBoldFormat}~The Orphic Hymns, 71: To Melinoë {#QuoteBaseFormat}(Anonymous; A. Athanassakis translation)
      """
    }
  ]
}